Commentary: Shape and bounce straightaway for the left-arm seamer. It is full, wide of off, moving away with some extra bounce. Dean Elgar keeps his bat to himself.
On a good length, width on offer. Dean Elgar shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.

Dean Elgar and South Africa are off the mark now! It is too full and straight down leg. Dean Elgar clips it past Head at short leg. They take two with ease as the fielder at deep square leg cuts it out.
A length ball, outside off, moving away. Elgar has no shot to offer.
This is full straying on the pads, Dean Elgar stays back and clips it through the gap at mid-wicket. They take three before the fielder chases it down.
Mitchell Starc ends his first over with a full delivery, around off, nipping away. Sarel Erwee gets behind the line and blocks it out.
This is on a good length, on leg stump. This one skids through. Dean Elgar gets it behind square off the outer half. They cross for one.
A dot now! Full and on off, angling across. Erwee blocks it out with a straight bat.
Two dots on the trot! This is on a good length, in the channel. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms.
Make that three! Pat Cummins serves a short ball, down leg. Sarel Erwee lets it be as it too far.
Sarel Erwee is yet to get off the mark here. It is on a good length, on off. Erwee closes the face and blocks it to short leg.

Just a single off the over then! An excellent start by Cummins. It is a length ball, angled across outside off. The ball nips in a touch off the deck. Although, Sarel Erwee reads the bounce well and makes the leave.
An outswinging delivery, fuller, wide of off. Dean Elgar lets it sail past him.
Shorter, wide of off. Elgar is happy with a sighter here as he leaves it alone.
Length, on leg. Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket and gets across for a quick single.

Sarel Erwee opens his account with a single. It is full, on middle and leg. Sarel Erwee plays the on drive and gets it to the right of mid on. Pat Cummins moves to that side and makes a solid stop with a dive. The batters take one.
BEATEN! An outswinger, wide of off. Dean Elgar tries to block it out but gets beaten in the process.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Touch fuller, on leg stump. Sarel Erwee tries to flick it through the leg side but takes a huge blow high on his pads.
This length ball is pushed to covers for one.
Outside off, onf ifth stump, angling away. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Dean Elgar blocks this length ball back to the bowler.

DROPPED! A tough chance nonetheless. It is a full-length ball, on off. Dean Elgar tries to flick it away but miscues it to the left of the bowler. It is in the air for a short while but Pat Cummins could not make the most of it.
Length, on fourth stump. Elgar kets it be.
Good length, around off. Erwee blocks it into covers.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Sarel Erwee takes a blow high on his pads. Mitchell Starc appeals but the umpire shows no interest.
Mitchell Starc makes a loud appeal once again. It is much fuller, on middle and leg. Erwee tries to flick it away but misses.
It is full and wide outside off. Sarel Erwee leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for three runs.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Elgar hangs back and tries to flick it away. He gets it back to the bowler off his pads.
On off, blocked out.
Good length, in the channel, left alone.
This is outside off once again. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
Fuller in length, on off, pushed out.
FOUR! This one flies past the keeper. Fraction short, sliding down leg. Sarel Erwee stays back and pulls it past the diving keeper for four runs.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! It is touch full, on leg. Sarel Erwee stays back and clips it over mid-wicket for another boundary.
A loud appeal for caught behind is turned down. There was surely some noise on the way. It is a length ball, in the channel. It shapes away a touch and Erwee gets beatan on the outside edge.
This is full and on off. Elgar pushes it to cover for one.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Good length, outside off, moving away. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
Length ball, on top of off. Sarel Erwee gets on his front foot and defends it out solidly.
This is in the channel, swinging away. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Just a single off the over. Fraction short, wide outside off. Elgar has no shot to offer.
Pat Cummins dishes a length ball, on fifth stump, nips in a bit late. Dean Elgar trusts the bounce and makes a solid leave.
Around off, defended out.
Pat Cummins angles this into the pads. Dean Elgar looks to tuck it away but he gets a thick inside edge on his pads.
Fuller, on off. Dean Elgar drives it to the right of the bowler.
Too straight, attacking the pads. Elgar pushes it out to safety.
Pat Cummins records his first maiden of the innings, Good length, on off. Dean Elgar keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it out.
Scott Boland comes 'round the wicket and goes short, wide of off. Sarel Erwee cuts it to point but straight to the fielder.
A single now as Sarel Erwee knocks this full ball into covers.
Full and on off, pushed to extra covers.
Good length, wide of off. Left alone.
Slightly short, on off. Elgar taps it to cover and scampers across for a quick single. It could've been a risky run.
Fuller, shaped back into the batter. Sarel Erwee knocks it back to the bowler. A tidy start by Boland.
Good length, anglded into the batter, on off. Dean Elgar defends it out on his front foot.
Full length, on off. Elgar blocks it back to Pat Cummins.
Short ball, going down leg. Dean Elgar gets inside the line and tries to chase it but misses.
Overpitched, wide of off. Dean Elgar drives it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee moves to 18. Very full, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee gets on his front foot and drives it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Sarel Erwee gets pinged high on his pads.
This is on a good length just outside off, Dean Elgar lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Goes a touch fuller and around leg, Dean Elgar nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
BEAUTY! Scott Boland serves this on a hand length and on the sixth stump line, shaping away a shy bit, Sarel Erwee looks to block it out, but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TAKEN! Scott Boland draws first blood! The crowd is going absolutely berserk over here. Scott Boland bowls another good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away again, Sarel Erwee this time goes for the drive away from his body, but gets an outside edge towards the slip cordon where Usman Khawaja takes a sharp low catch. Sarel Erwee is not happy with himself as he could have easliy left this one alone. South Africa lose their first!
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Scott Boland

Commentary: On a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn guides it with the outer half of his bat towards point.
Fuller one, on middle, swinging in, Theunis de Bruyn misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads towards the leg side. End of a successful over for the Aussies!
Nathan Lyon starts with a tossed up delivery, short and on off, Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Floated, short and on off, turning away a bit, Dean Elgar blocks it to the off side.
Shorter again and outside off, Dean Elgar goes on his back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a brace.
Nathan Lyon continues with his shorter length, on off, Dean Elgar steers it towards point.
Shortish and on off again, Dean Elgar knocks it off the back foot towards point.
A single to end the over as this short delivery is forced to the left of point by Elgar.

Oh..this is close! Scott Boland bowls this back of a length and on middle, angling in, Dean Elgar looks to block it out but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls towards the stumps. It just kisses the bottom of the off pole, but there is not enough power to knock the bails off. Elgar survives.
This is pitched up, on off, Dean Elgar drills it wide of short covers where the fielder dives to his right to make a one-handed stop.
FOUR! Nice shot! Scott Boland serves this full again and on off, Dean Elgar stays there and drives it well wide of short covers and towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Dean Elgar pushes it towards covers.
On a length and on off, Dean Elgar defends it towards point.
BEATEN! Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and around off, straightens a bit after hitting the deck, Dean Elgar gets squared up and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter, short and on middle, grips and turns a long way to the leg side, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone and the leg slip parries it behind the keeper. A bye is taken.
Floated, short and on off, Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Darts this one full and on the pads, Dean Elgar tucks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
Flighted, full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn leans on and defends it down the pitch.
Theunis de Bruyn gets off the mark now! This is short and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn moves onto his back foot quickly and pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Scott Boland comes 'over the wicket and bowls this on a hard length, on off, angling in, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
This is a touch fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn goes to drive it but gets an outside edge and the ball goes on the bounce towards gully.
Full again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn guides it towards gully again.
Short of a length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn cuts it through point for a couple of runs.
Goes fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn is solid in his defense.
This is on a good length and around off, Theunis de Bruyn leans on and lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Dean Elgar drives it towards mid on.
Short and well outside off, Dean Elgar cuts it but straight to point. He missed out there as this was a poor delivery.
Floated, full and on off, turning away, Dean Elgar leans on and slices it a bit towards covers.
Shorter in length and on off, Dean Elgar punches it towards covers.
Another dot! This is flighted, full and on off, Dean Elgar drives it towards cover again.
A maiden over! Nathan Lyon bowls this short and on off, Dean Elgar taps it but finds covers again.
Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and on the fifth stump line, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
This is full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn defends it in front of point.
Full again and around off, Theunis de Bruyn watches it carefully and makes a good leave.
Scott Boland is sticking to his good length and outside off line, Theunis de Bruyn is happy to let it go to the keeper once again.
Another one! This is on a good length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
Two maiden overs in row then! Scott Boland serves this on a hard length and on off, angling in, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.

Almost a wicket on the first ball for Green! He starts with a full delivery, outside off, Dean Elgar slices it uppishly towards point where Nathan Lyon dives to his left but only manages to get finger tips of his left hand. They cross.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn stays there and shows the full face of the bat to drive it straight past the bowler for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! This is a poor delivery though as Green bowls this on a hard length and on the pads, Theunis de Bruyn tickles it towards the fine leg fence for another boundary.
This is on a good length and just ouside off, Theunis de Bruyn lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn steers it towards point.
Fuller one and on off, Theunis de Bruyn strokes it towards mid off.
Short of a length and on leg, Dean Elgar helps it towards fine leg for a single.
Scott Boland once again bowls this on a good length and on off, shaping in a bit, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn works it towards mid on for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, Dean Elgar looks to play at it, but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards slip cordon.
Back of a length and around off, Dean Elgar blocks it out to the off side.

FOUR! Good shot! Scott Boland comes around the wicket and serves this full, on middle, angling in, Dean Elgar stays there and drives it towards the vacant long off fence for a boundary. That also brings up 5000 runs for Elgar in Test cricket.
On a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn knocks it towards mid off.
Goes a bit fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
This is on a good length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn works it towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone once again.
Extra bounce! Cameron Green bowls this back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn looks to upper cut it, but gets beaten by the extra bounce from the surface.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cameron Green strikes now! He bowls this short of a length again and around off, Theunis de Bruyn stays there and goes for the pull shot, but gets an top edge as the ball flies in the air and behind the keeper. Alex Carey calls for it, settles under and takes a good catch. There was absolutely no need of that shot and Theunis de Bruyn has thrown his wicket away here. South Africa two down now!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: On a length and outside off, Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, Dean Elgar works it towards mid on.
Back of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar gets hurried and blocks it towards mid-wicket.
This is on a hard length and around off, Dean Elgar looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller one and on the pads, Dean Elgar nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and on middle, Temba Bavuma tucks it towards square leg for a single and gets off the mark.

Wow...that could have easily been a wicket! Pat Cummins bowls this on a hard length and on off, gets some extra bounce of the surface, Temba Bavuma does really well to keep it down as he gets hit on his gloves.
This is on a good length and outside off, Temba Bavuma looks to block it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length and on middle, Temba Bavuma defends it well this time.
Fuller one and outside off, Temba Bavuma lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and on off, extra bounce again, Temba Bavuma watches it through and blocks it with the outer half of his bat to the off side.
Full and on off, Temba Bavuma drives it towards the bowler where Pat Cummins goes down and gets a hand to it as he parries it towards mid off.
On a length and on middle, Dean Elgar knocks it towards mid on.
Length again and on middle, Dean Elgar works it towards mid on again.
Short of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar stays back and mistimes his push towards mid off.
Not sure what Elgar is upto here! This is back of a length and on middle, Dean Elgar thinks about the pull shot, but decides against and it awkwardly pushes it towards covers.

OUT! RUN OUT! A disaster for South Africa! Dean Elgar has gifted his wicket with a lapse of judgement here. Mitchell Starc bowl this on a hard length and on off, Dean Elgar punches it to the right of mid off and set off for the run. However, Marnus Labuschagne there and runs onto the ball in a flash, picks it up and hits bullseye at the non-striker's end and Elgar is well short of his crease. The replays confirms the same. South Africa in trouble now just before Lunch.
Howout: run out (Marnus Labuschagne)

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Two in two balls for Australia and they are well and truly on top here! Temba Bavuma goes back to the hut for a low score. Mitchell Starc bowls this on a hard length and around off with some away movement, Temba Bavuma looks to poke at it from his crease, but only manages to get a thin outside edge towards the keeper where Alex Carey takes a good catch moving to his right. South Africa four down before Lunch now!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: This is on a good length and on off, Khaya Zondo moves across and blocks it out.
Length again and outside off, Khaya Zondo leaves it alone.
Pat Cummins continues to bowl on a good length, outside off again, Khaya Zondo shoulders arms.
Fuller one and on off, Khaya Zondo drills it back towards the bowler.
Pat Cummins bangs this short and on off, Khaya Zondo sways out of the line of it.
On a length and on off, Khaya Zondo strokes it towards point. That will be Lunch!
Mitchell Starc starts with a full one, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards mid on.
Kyle Verreynne stays back to this full delivery and defends it to the leg side.
Three dots in a row! It is overpitched, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to the off side, not in the gap though.
Make that four! It is a length ball, on off. This one stays low a touch and nips into the batter from outside off. Kyle Verreynne comes forward and defends it out.
Slightly shorter, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne tries to go for the cut shot but gets beaten in the process.
FOUR! Top placement. It is a  half-volley, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne gets on his front foot and squeezes it past backward point for a boundary.
Full length, around leg. Zondo blocks it towards mid on.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Zondo shuffles and taps it to covers.
Very full, wide of off. Zondo hits it through the line and drives it through the off side. The batters take two with ease.
Zondo flicks this full delivery into mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
On a length, on off. This one stays low. Kyle Verreynne gets his blade down in time to defend it out.
Touch short, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne lets it be. Just three runs off the over.
Starc serves a short ball, outside off. Zondo leaves it alone for the keeper.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, angling across the right-hander. Khaya Zondo looks to ride the bounce and cut it away but misses.
On off, blocked out to safety.
Four dots in a row! It is a sharp bouncer, around off. Zondo sways away from the line of delivery.
Make it five! Good length, on the pads, Zondo clips it towards mid-wicket. Will Starc be able to complete his maiden over?
Yes, he does! Second maiden for the seamer. It is full and on off. Zondo drives it straight to the man at mid off.
This is a length ball that lands outside off and nips in a bit. Kyle Verreynne closes the face and blocks it away.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne stays back and tucks it to the right of the bowler.
Too full and straight, Kyle Verreynne defends this full delivery back to the bowler.
Another dot! A length ball, around the hips. Kyle Verreynne comes inside the line and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length and on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it to covers off the front foot.
Pat Cummins gets his fourth maiden so far. It is a length ball, on fifth stump. Kyle Verreynne gets behind the line and blocks it out to safety.

How has this missed the stumps? Khaya Zondo almost chops on! It is a length ball, angled across the right-hander. Khaya Zondo tries to leave it away but is a tad late. The ball hit the deck and luckily, it goes past the stumps.
This full delivery is driven through covers for a couple now.

OUT! CAUGHT!! Mitchell Starc gets the first wicket in the post-Lunch session and the crowd is loving it. A full-length ball, angling across, outside off. Khaya Zondo tries to drive it through the line but does so aerially. It goes to the left of extra cover. Marnus Labuschagne places there dives to his left and takes a sharp low catch to break this stand.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and on off, angling away, Marco Jansen looks to play at it but get beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller one and on off, Marco Jansen drives it past short covers for a brace and gets off the mark.
Mitchell Starc bangs in a bouncer, on leg, Marco Jansen ducks under it.

IN THE AIR! It lands safely though. It is a short ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne tries to pull it away without any foot movement. The ball takes a thick outside edge and goes high in the air towards square leg. Alex Carey gives it a chase from behind the sticks but could not get there in time. One taken.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Marco Jansen ducks under it.
JAFFA! It is a length ball, outside off, it shapes away a touch off the deck. Marco Jansen tries to block it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, on off, tucked to the leg side.
Good length, in the channel. It flies off the deck. Marco Jansen keeps his bat to himself.
Just a single of the over then. Quite full, on off. Jansen flicks it to mid-wicket.
Angling across the right-hander, on a length. Kyle Verreynne lets it be.
Quite full and close to the batter, around off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it into covers.
Starc goes full, wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne guides it through cover-point for a couple this time.
Good length, on off, tapped to point.
OUCH! A bodyblow this time. Mitchell Starc bends his back hard and serves a sharp bouncer on off. Kyle Verreynne turns around and takes a blow on his shoulders.
Good length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and punches it through point for two runs.
A dot to start with! Touch short, on middle and leg. Jansen goes back and defends it into covers.
Length, just outside off, blocked back to the bowler.
Quite short, wide of off. Marco Jansen leaves it alone for the keeper.
OUCH! A nasty blow! Back of a length, on off. The ball flies off the deck. Marco Jansen thinks of ducking under it but is a bit late. The ball sneaks through his arms and hits him near his face.
On off, pushed to covers.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Jansen drives it to long on and takes a single.
A length ball, nipping in from outside off. Jansen blocks it on his front foot.
TWO LEG BYES! Very full, angling down leg. Jansen misses his flick and it goes down to fine leg. They collect two leg byes.
Good length, outside of. Marco Jansen slashes at it but misses.
This is down leg. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Quite full, outside off, shaping a bit while staying low. Jansen gets beaten in the process.
Marco Jansen blocks this full delivery on his front foot to get this over to an end.
Green goes for a yorker length delivery, on off. Kyle Verreynne digs it out in time.
Length, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and puhses it to point for one.
On middle and leg, blocked to mid on.

A length ball, around off, nips away off the deck. Marco Jansen fails to defend it out and the ball goes through the gap between the keeper and first slip. The batters collect a leg bye, as it comes off the pads of Jansen.
Outside off, left alone.
Short, on off. Kyle Verreynne pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
This is on a good length and on middle, Marco Jansen works it uppishly just past Travis Head at short leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Nice timing! Scott Boland serves this full and on off, Marco Jansen stays there and just gently strokes it towards the long off fence for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Marco Jansen knocks it towards covers.
Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and outside off, Marco Jansen lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Length again and on off, Marco Jansen blocks it to the off side.
A bit fuller and on off, Marco Jansen leans on and defends it towards mid off.
Back of a length and on middle, Kyle Verreynne tucks it to the right of mid on for a single.
Fuller one and around off, shaping away, Marco Jansen goes for the drive, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full again and on middle, Marco Jansen flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Cameron Green bangs in a bouncer, on off, Marco Jansen sways away from the line of it.
Goes back to his fuller length, on middle, Marco Jansen drills it towards mid on.
Short of a length and on off, swinging away, Marco Jansen drops his hands and lets it go to the keeper.
Short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Scott Boland bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, shaping in, Marco Jansen ducks under it as Alex Carey collects it moving to his left.
Back of a length and on off, Marco Jansen shoulders arms to it.
This is a touch fuller and on middle, angling in, Marco Jansen misses his flick as the ball deflects off his pads to the off side.
On a length and on off, shaping in, Marco Jansen judges it well and leaves it alone.
Full and on off, Marco Jansen blocks it towards short covers.
Cameron Green lands this on a good length and on off, Kyle Verreynne blocks it towards short covers.
Full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne drives it back towards the bowler.
Full again but down the pads this time, Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length and on off, shaping away, Marco Jansen offers no shot at it.
On a length and on middle, Marco Jansen strokes it towards mid on.
Short of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen gets on top of it and blocks it down the pitch.
Full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne moves across and nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, Marco Jansen gets behind the line of it and defends it back to the bowler.
Length again and around leg, Marco Jansen knocks it towards mid-wicket and denies for the run.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Marco Jansen pushes it towards covers.
Fuller again and on off, Marco Jansen is solid in his defense again.
Back of a length and outside off, Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne drives it towards mid off.
This is on a good length and on middle, Kyle Verreynne looks to flick it, but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW, but turned down.
On a length and on leg, Kyle Verreynne works it in front of mid on for a quick single.
Pitched up, on off, Marco Jansen drives it firmly but straight towards mid off.
Cameron Green bangs in a bouncer, on middle and leg, Marco Jansen ducks underneath it.
Back of a length and on off, Marco Jansen blocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length and on leg, Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Fine shot! This is full and on middle, Marco Jansen makes some room and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. 100 up for South Africa!
This is back of a length and on leg, Marco Jansen looks to play at it, but misses and gets hit on his stomach area.
Mitchell Starc bowls a fiery bouncer now, on middle, Marco Jansen sways away from it.
Mitchell Starc serves this full and down the leg, Marco Jansen misses his flick as Alex Carey collects it moving to his left.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and on middle, Marco Jansen looks to sway away from it, but the ball takes the outer edge and rolls towards gully.
Flatter, short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne knocks it towards short leg.
Tossed up, on middle, Kyle Verreynne uses his feet and tucks it towards widish mid on for a single.
Floated, short and on middle, Marco Jansen moves back and defends it to the leg side.
Flighted, short and on off, turning in sharply, Marco Jansen looks to flick it away, but misses and the ball goes off his pads towards point.
Quicker one, full and outside off, Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Tossed up, full and on off, Marco Jansen leans on and blocks it out.
Back of a length and on off, Kyle Verreynne punches it well wide of deep point for three runs.
Full and on leg, Marco Jansen keeps it out to the off side.
Full again and well outside off, anglin away, Marco Jansen offers no shot at it.
Short of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen knocks it towards mid on.
Goes full and on middle, Marco Jansen drives it back towards the bowler where Mitchell Starc goes down and collects it.
On a length and on middle, Marco Jansen works it with the inner half towards mid on.
Floated, short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne blocks it towards short leg.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is short again and on middle, Kyle Verreynne quickly moves onto his back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
A bit short and on middle again, Kyle Verreynne forces it towards mid on for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Marco Jansen tucks it towards deep square leg for one.
Quicker, full and on off, Kyle Verreynne looks to cut it away, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Shortish and on middle, Kyle Verreynne pushes it back towards the bowler.
This is on a good length and on middle, Marco Jansen knocks it with the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Marco Jansen drives it through covets for a brace as Marnus Labuschagne chases it and keeps it in.
This is on a hard length and on off, angling away, Marco Jansen looks to block it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller one and on off, Marco Jansen drills it towards short covers.
Back of a length and on off, Marco Jansen steers it towards gully.
FOUR! Good shot! This is full and on middle, Marco Jansen stays there and powerfully drives it towards the long on fence for a boundary.
A bit short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter, short and outside off, Kyle Verreynne looks to cut it, but bunts it onto the ground.
Shortish and on middle, Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Half chance! This is quicker, short and on middle, Marco Jansen tucks it uppishly towards short leg where Marnus Labuschagne fails to grab hold of it low to his right.
FOUR! Nice use of the feet! This is tossed up and around middle, Marco Jansen dances down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Nathan Lyon bowls this quicker, full and on middle, Marco Jansen goes down and sweeps it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, mistimes his push towards mid on for a single.
Back of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen does well to keep it down to the leg side.
Short of a length and on leg, Marco Jansen works it towards square leg where Usman Khawaja allows a run with a misfield.
Short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Full and on off, Marco Jansen drives it towards short covers.
Back of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle, Kyle Verreynne comes down the track and drives it towards mid on for a single.
Floated, short and on off, turning in, Marco Jansen blocks it out.
Flighted, full and on off, Marco Jansen pushes it towards mid off.
Flatter, full and on middle, Marco Jansen defends it towards square leg.
Looped up, short and on off, Marco Jansen leans on and blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Marco Jansen is solid in his defense again.
Short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne pulls it through square leg for a single.
Short again and on off, Marco Jansen goes for the pull shot, but toe-ends it towards mid on in the end.
Back of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen blocks it towards short leg.
Back of a length again, on middle, Marco Jansen defends it to the leg side.
Pat Cummins lands this short and on off, Marco Jansen is through his pull shot early again, but toe-ends it towards slip this time.
Pat Cummins continues with his shorter length and on middle, Marco Jansen is in two minds to whether to pull it or not, and in the end gets hit on his arms.
Flatter, short and on middle, turning in to the leg side, Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Floated, full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Marco Jansen sweeps it to square leg for one.
Shortish and on middle, Kyle Verreynne moves back and helps it towards fine leg forn one more.
Gives this one some air, on middle, Marco Jansen works it past short leg for a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne reverse-sweeps it through cover-point for three runs.
Short and on leg, Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Short of a length and on middle, Marco Jansen gets on top of it and blocks it out.
A good bouncer this time, on middle and leg, Marco Jansen lets it go to the keeper.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is on a good length and on off, Marco Jansen looks to block it with soft hands but gets an outside edge towards the third man fence for a boundary.

DROPPED! The plan almost worked for the Aussies! Pat Cummins lands this short and on middle, Marco Jansen pulls it uppishly towards square leg where Usman Khawaja dives to his left, gets both hands but spills it. They cross. Marco Jansen has been given a life here.
On a length and on middle, Kyle Verreynne moves across and knocks it towards mid-wicket. That will be Tea!
FOUR! Nicely played. It is floated and full, on leg. Marco Jansen gets low and sweeps this behind square on the leg side for a boundary. He moves to 42 with this one.
On middle and leg, blocked out watchfully.
This is looped up, turning down leg. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.

Half-a-chance! Shouts of catch but it lands safe. It is pushed through quicker, around middle and leg. Marco Jansen comes down the track and gets an inside edge on his pads. The ball goes aerially to the right of the bowler, but it lands safely, even the short leg could not react quicker.
On off, blocked out.
This is tossed up, on off. Marco Jansen pads it out.
Boland starts with a length ball that comes in from outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back inside his crease and flicks it down to fine leg. They cross for a couple.
Kyle Verreynne blocks this length ball solidly.

A loud appeal for caught behind! Steven Smith at second slip is very animated, although the bowler shows no interest. The umpire is unmoved. Pat Cummins thinks it is close enough and takes the review. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball, in the channel of uncertainty. It shapes away a bit. Kyle Verreynne hangs his blade away from his body in an attempt to block it away but gets beaten on the outside edge. The Australian fielders though seem to be exicted but it was cut short after the review confirms that there was no bat involved.
Short, on off, defended out.
This is outside off, left alone by Kyle Verreynne.
It is quite full, outside off. Kyle Verreynne makes a good leave this time.
Floated and full, outside off. Marco Jansen drives it into covers.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Marco Jansen presses forward and defends it to the leg side.
A single now as this full delivery is swept away behind square on the leg side.
Flatter, wide of off, turning in a touch. Kyle Verreynne reads it well and early to make an easy leave.
This is short, on leg stump. Kyle Verreynne gets inside the line and flicks it past short fine leg.
Flatter one, on leg. Kyle Verreynne nudges it to square leg. A tidy over from Lyon comes to an end.
Boland starts with an in-tucker, full and on leg. Jansen stays back and clips it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, coming in from outside off. Marco Jansen blocks it inside the deck.
Length, on top of off, blocked out solidly.
Short ball, on the body. Jansen flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Kyle Verreynne gets across and blocks this good length delivery.
Outside off, left alone.
Pushed through quicker, full and on leg. Marco Jansen gets down on one knee and sweeps it down to deep square leg but only for a single as there is protection in the deep.
Turning in from outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets across and nudges it to the leg side.
Short one, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it through point for a single.
This is much fuller, on off. Marco Jansen gets squared up this time. It takes a thick outside edge but it does not carry to the man at first slip as it is played with soft hands.
This is tossed up, on off. It gets some extra bounce. Marco Jansen fails to defend it away and it comes off the thigh pads. It goes past short leg.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Much fuller, on off. Kyle Verreynne leans in and drives it to sweeper cover for two runs.
A length ball, outside off, nips in a long way. Kyle Verreynne works it to fine leg and crosses. Scott Boland has to reload this delivery as he oversteps. This stand moves to 91.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marco Jansen steps across and defends it out.
A length ball, on top of off. Marco Jansen closes the face of the bat and flicks it to the leg side.
This is sliding down leg. Marco Jansen fails to work it around the corner. It hits him on his pads on the way out.
A surprise short ball, on the body. Marco Jansen defends it awkwardly towards fine leg. They take one as it goes in the gap.

EDGED! It is a good-length ball, on off. It flies off the deck. Kyle Verreynne thinks of riding the bounce and goes for the pull shot. All he manages to get is a thick inside edge which goes to the man at first slip off his pads.
BEATEN! It is tossed up, wide of off. Marco Jansen is drawn to play this one. He tries to drive it through the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Much fuller, on off, turning in as well. Marco Jansen gets it to the le side off the inner half.

FOUR! Almost a chance. Marco Jansen moves to his FIFTY! This is is first half-century in Test cricket. It is looped up, on middle, Jansen dances down the track and lofts it towards long on. Mitchell Starc runs to his left in the deep. He dives to that side but could not time his jump well to catch the ball. The ball races away to the boundary.
On off, defended to short leg.

FOUR! Marco Jansen makes it worse for Lyon as he gets his second boundary in the over. It is turning down leg. Marco Jansen stays back and glances it around the corner for a boundary at fine leg. This partnership is now worth 100.
Full length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets on his front foot and strokes it to covers.
This is a length ball, angling down leg. Kyle Verreynne goes for the flick but misses. A few fans in the crowd were surely interested though.
A length ball, on top of off. Kyle Verreynne defends it back to the bowler.
On off, Kyle Verreynne gets forward and helps it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, on leg. Kyle Verreynne clips it through mid-wicket for three runs.
Flatter one, outside off, turning in. Kyle Verreynne gets across and blocks it out.

FIFTY FOR VERREYNNE! This has been an gritty knock from him and he has put his team in a decent position here. He will look convert this into a big score now. This is tossed up, on middle, Kyle Verreynne uses his feet and drives it towards long on for a run.
FOUR! Very full, wide of off. Marco Jansen leans in and caresses it through covers for a fine boundary. He seems to be in good touch here.
On leg, defended out.
Tosses it up, on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Jansen times his drive well but finds mid off.
Short ball, outside off. left alone.
Good length, on off, climbing on the batter. Kyle Verreynne opens the face late and plays it to gully.
Full, on off, defended out.
Four dots on the trot now! It is full, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid off by walking down the track.
On a length, on fourth stump. Kyle Verreynne pushes it into covers.
On a good length, wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne stay back and leaves it alone for the keeper. A maiden over by Green comes to an end.
Floated, short and on middle, turning in, Marco Jansen lets it hit his pads.
A bit short and on off, Marco Jansen pushes it towards covers.
Quicker one, full and on middle, Marco Jansen blocks it out.
Flatter, full and on of, Marco Jansen drives it on the up towards covers.
Tossed up, short and on off, turning in, Marco Jansen blocks it down the pitch.
Another maiden over! This is flighted and around off, Marco Jansen leans on and defends it on the front foot.
This is on a good length and on middle, Kyle Verreynne knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Kyle Verreynne drives it towards the bowler where Green gets a hand to it and parries it towards mid off.
Back of a length and outside off, Kyle Verreynne cuts it towards deep point for a single.
Short and on middle, Marco Jansen defends it off the back foot.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Marco Jansen tries to drive it away, but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Cameron Green bangs this short and on middle, Marco Jansen ducks under it and Alex Carey behind the stumps only manages to get some glove on it as the ball rolls behind him towards the fence. Steven Smith from slip chases it and keeps it inside after a fumble. Two byes taken!
Floated, short and on middle, turning in, Kyle Verreynne helps it towards short fine leg.
Short again and on middle, Kyle Verreynne knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter, full and on off, turning in, Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
Shortish and on middle, Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne eases it towards long on for a single.
Quicker, full and on leg, turning further to the leg side, Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on off, Kyle Verreynne pushes it back to the bowler.
A good bouncer, on middle, Kyle Verreynne ducks under it and Alex Carey leaps up to collect it.
Full and on middle, Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Kyle Verreynne blocks it to the off side.

OUT! TAKEN! Cameron Green finally gets the breakthrough! Australian players are relieved to see the back of Kyle Verreynne here. Cameron Green bowls this on a good length and just around off, Kyle Verreynne prods forward to defend, but gets a thin outside edge towards Steven Smith at slips who makes no mistake. The huge partnership is finally broken and South Africa are six down now.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Cameron Green

Commentary: Full and outside off, Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.
Fires this one full and on the pads, Marco Jansen flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on off, Keshav Maharaj blocks it with inside edge onto his pads.
Tossed up, short and on middle, turning in, Keshav Maharaj misses his flick as the ball loops up off his pads and the leg slip pouches it. There is an appeal for catch but turned down.
Quicker, short and on middle, turning to the leg side, Keshav Maharaj leaevs it alone.
Flighted, full and on middle, Keshav Maharaj moves on his back foot and defends it on the pitch.
Short and on middle, Keshav Maharaj makes room and cuts it off the back foot through cover-point for a brace and gets off the mark.

EDGED AND GONE! Cameron Green with a double strike here! He sends both the set batters back to the hut in consecutive overs. He serves this on a fuller length and on the fifth stump line, Marco Jansen goes for the drive on the up without any footwork, but the shape away takes the outside edge of his bat and goes towards the keeper where Alex Carey takes a comfortable catch. Marco Jansen played well, but he has to make that long walk back. South Africa lose their seventh.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: On a length and on off, Kagiso Rabada guides it towards point.
FOUR! Kagiso Rabada opens his account with a boundary! This is full and outside off, Kagiso Rabada steers it in the gap and towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Full again and on off, Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards covers.
Short of a length and on off, Kagiso Rabada lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Cameron Green gets another one in this over! He picks up his fourth wicket and Australia have made a good comeback in this game. Green bowls this short of a length again and on of, Kagiso Rabada is in two minds whether to play it or leave it, and just keeps his bat there hanging. The ball takes the inside edge and rattle onto the stumps. Kagiso Rabada just stays there in disappointment. South Africa eight down now!
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Flatter, short and on off, Keshav Maharaj looks to poke at it, but misses it completely.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Keshav Maharaj leans on and blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! Nathan Lyon gets his first wicket now. He filghts this one up, full and on off, Keshav Maharaj looks to take him on and goes for the big shot, but he miscues it badly as the ball flies in the air behind mid off where Pat Cummins trackbacks a bit, settles under it and completes the catch. South Africa are just throwing their wickets away here.
Howout: c Pat Cummins b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Darts this one full and on middle, Lungi Ngidi blocks it out.
On off, defended.
Floated, full and on off, Lungi Ngidi knocks it to the off side.
Full and on middle, Anrich Nortje tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Cameron Green bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, Lungi Ngidi ducks underneath it.
Full and on off, Lungi Ngidi drives it past mid off and gets a couple of runs.

OUT! TIMBER! FIVE-FER FOR GREEN! He has destroyed the South African lower middle-order here. This time he bowls it fuller and around off, straightens a bit, Lungi Ngidi makes room and tries to drive again, but misses the ball completely and loses his off pole. South Africa have been bowled out for 189!
Howout: b Cameron Green

Commentary: Kagiso Rabada errs in his line a bit and starts with a short delivery down the leg, David Warner misses his pull shot.
Kagiso Rabada bangs in a bouncer now, on leg, David Warner ducks under it.
Kagiso Rabada continues with the shorter length but this is down the leg too, David Warner leaves it alone.
Short and way down the leg side, David Warner lets it go to the keeper. He needs to make Warner play.
Another easy leave for Warner! This is a bit full but down the leg again, David Warner offers no shot at it.
Another full delivery, on leg, David Warner thinks about the flick, but decides against it in the end. Not a good start for Kagiso Rabada.
Lungi Ngidi starts with a good-length delivery, on off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
On a length and on off, Usman Khawaja gets square up and knocks it with the outer half towards point.
Goes fuller this time but way outside off, Usman Khawaja shoulders arms to it.
Full again and on middle, angling in, Usman Khawaja blocks it back to the bowler.
Lungi Ngidi continues with his fuller length and outside off, Usman Khawaja offers no shot at it.
A maiden over then! This is on a hard length and on off, angling in, Usman Khawaja once again lets it go to the keeper.
Australia and David Warner are underway in style! Kagiso Rabada lands this short and around leg, David Warner swivels and pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Short of a length and down the leg, shaping further away, David Warner leaves it alone and Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps dives to his right to collect it. A good take from the keeper.
Full and on off, David Warner drives it firmly but straight to short covers.
Full again and on middle this time, David Warner drills it towards mid on.
Short of a length and on middle, David Warner hops a bit and gets an inside edge as the ball goes nowhere.
This is pitched up, on the pads, David Warner flicks it towards the vacant deep square leg region for three runs.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, way outside off, David Warner makes an easy leave.
Full and on middle, shaping in, David Warner watches it through and pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner cuts it towards the cover region for a single.
Short of a length and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends it to the right of short leg.
Fuller one and on off, Usman Khawaja drives it straight to short covers.
This is on a good length and outside off, Usman Khawaja offers no shot at it.
Full and outside off, David Warner mistimes his drive back towards the bowler.
Back of a length and on middle, David Warner works it with the inner half through square leg and comes back for the second.
Length again and on off, David Warner steers it towards point.
Full and on off, David Warner pushes it towards covers.
FOUR! Nice shot! Kagiso Rabada bangs this short, on middle, but it sits up nicely for the batter, David Warner pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and outside off, David Warner punches it behind point for three more runs.
Short of a length and on off, shaping in, David Warner pushes it towards covers and denies for the single.
Short again and outside off, angling away, David Warner leaves it alone this time.
Lungi Ngidi continues bowling short and outside off, David Warner bunts it onto the ground to the off side.
This is on a good length and on off, David Warner lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Length again and on middle, David Warner knocks it towards mid on,
A bit fuller and on off,, David Warner drops it in front of short covers and calls for the run but his partner sends him back.
Full length, angled across, Usman Khawaja pushes it through covers with soft hands. They cross.
Good length, on leg stump. David Warner flicks it off his hips to square leg. The batters push hard and get two runs.
Fraction short, sliding down leg. David Warner tries to glance it, but misses as the ball goes off his pads towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada brings pin drop silence in the stadium now as he gets rid of Usman Khawaja on just 1. This is a huge wicket for South Africa. It is a length ball, angling across the left-hander. Usman Khawaja is drawn into the shot. He tries to block it out but hangs his blade way away from his body. The ball takes a thick outside edge and flies to the left of the keeper. Kyle Verreynne moves to that side and pouches the ball. South Africa will hope to build on this early wicket.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Full length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets on his front foot and defends it to mid on.
This is fuller, wide of off, shaping away. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone. A successful over from Rabada comes to an end.
Very full, outside off, at 133kmph. David Warner leans in and drives it through cover-point.Two taken.
Short, wide of off. Warner goes back and cuts it to point.
Outside off, on a fuller length, left alone by Warner.
Too full and straight attacking the off pole. David Warner blocks it to covers for one.
This is outside off, left alone.
FOUR LEG BYES! It is a length ball, going down leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets pinged on his thigh pads as he misses his flick. It races down to the fine leg fence.
NO BALL! Rabada nails a yorker this time. David Warner is up to the task as he digs it out back to the bowler. Rabada oversteps and he needs to reload this delivery.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! Gorgeous cover drive. It is full and outside off. David Warner times his drive well and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Too full, down leg. Warner nudges it to mid-wicket.
David Warner defends this length ball solidly.
Length and on off stump. David Warner pushes it out to safety.
This is down leg, left alone by Warner.
A length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it watchfully.
Fraction short, goind down leg. Marnus Labuschagne tries to go after it but fails to do so.
Length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Much fuller, outside off, angling away from the right-hand. Marnus Labuschagne tries to drive it away on his front foot but gets it to mid on off the inner half.
This is outside off and Marnus Labuschagne has no interest in playing away from his body.
This one is angled into the batter, on a length. Marnus Labuschagne goes back and flicks it through mid-wicket for two runs now.
A short ball, at 147 kmph, with some extra bounce off the deck. David Warner hops inside his crease and blocks it out.
A length ball, around middle, this one straightens a bit after hitting the deck. David Warner gets beaten on the inside edge.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
FOUR! Up and over! A short ball, wide of off. David Warner stands tall and cuts it over the slip cordon for four runs.
NO BALL! Good length, on leg. Warner clips it to mid-wicket for a couple. The umpire signals a no ball as the bower oversteps.
Length and on off, blocked out.
This one is outside off and Warner has no shot to offer.
Touch fuller, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it on his front foot.
Jansen goes full and on leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket. They take three.
Fraction short, on off, shaping away. David Warner decides to leave it a little too late and toe-ends it to the man at gully.
Quite short, wide of off, shaping away. David Warner tries to chase it but misses.
This is a length ball, around off. David Warner taps it to point.
A dot to end the over! It is full, attacking the stumps. David Warner presses forward and blocks it towards mid off. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Anrich Nortje starts with a short delivery and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne cuts it straight to point.
This is on a good length and outside off again, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
EDGE AND FOUR! Anrich Nortje serves this full and on off, Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive it on the up, but gets an outside edge as the ball flies between third slip and gully for a boundary.
A bit fuller and on off, keeps low, Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot at it and Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps also makes a half-stop. A bye is taken.
Back of a length and around off, David Warner punches it through covers for three runs.
BEAUTY! Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and on the fifth stump line, Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Nice shot! Kagiso Rabada lands this short and wide, David Warner accepts the width and cuts it past point for a boundary.
This is on a hard length but down the leg, David Warner leaves it alone.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle, shaping in, David Warner pushes it back to the bowler.
Short of a length and around off, David Warner steers it towards point.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and on off, angling away, David Warner lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller one and on the pads, David Warner tucks it through square leg and comes back for the second.
Back of a length and around off, Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot at it.
Touch fuller and outside off, shaping away a bit, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Short of a length and on off at 150 clicks, Marnus Labuschagne gets on top of it and blocks it back to the bowler.
This is on a hard length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
Full and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the off side.
Full again and on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it towards the vacant deep mid-wicket region for three runs.
On a length and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne knocks it to the right of mid on for a single.
Kagiso Rabada comes around the wicket and lands this short, on middle, David Warner pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
This is on a good length and around off, shaping away, Marnus Labuschagne wacthes it through and makes a good leave.
Length again and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length and on leg, angling in, David Warner helps it towards fine leg for one more.
Anrich Nortje also comes around the wicket and bowls this on a hard length, on off, David Warner dabs it toward point.
Goes fuller and on off, David Warner drives it firmly through covers for a triple. Marnus Labuschagne wants the fourth but he is sent back.
Back of a length and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne stays there and blocks it out.
Short of a length and outside off, shaping away, Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot at it.
This is on a good length and on off, nips back in sharply, Marnus Labuschagne looks to play at it, but misses and gets hit on his thigh pads.
A bit fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne moves across and defends it.
This is on a hard length and on the sixth stump line, David Warner lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and on middle, angling in, David Warner tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good shape! Kagiso Rabada serves this a touch fuller and around off, shaping away, Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot at it.
Length again and on off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
Short of a length and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne defends it to the leg side.
Looks like Rabada has got his rhythm back. He bowls this full and on off, shaping away, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
FOUR LEG BYES! Anrich Nortje bangs in a good bouncer, on middle, David Warner goes for the pull shot, but misses as the ball deflects off his helmet towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Anrich Nortje bangs in another sharp bouncer on middle and leg, David Warner this time ducks under it.

OUT! RUN OUT! A huge mix-up in the middle and Marnus Labuschagne sacrifices his wicket. South African players are delighted. Anrich Nortje bowls this on a hard length and on off, David Warner pushes it in front of covers and sets off for the run. The fielder there picks up and has a shy at the batter's end but misses as the ball rolls towards deep square leg. Marnus Labuschagne tries to go for the overthrow but he is well past the batting crease and Warner agrees, but both of them hesitate a bit in the middle. However, Marnus Labuschagne decides to go to the danger end and sacrifices his wicket as David Warner is a long way down the track. Keshav Maharaj throws the ball at the bowler's end where Anrich Nortje collects it and breaks the stumps with an underarm throw. Australia two down now!
Howout: run out (Keshav Maharaj / Anrich Nortje)

Commentary: Back of a length, just outside off. David Warner gets across and blocks it back to the bowler.
Length and outside off. Warner taps it to covers. The fielder dives to his left and makes a good stop. The batters only take a single.
A dot to end the over! On a good length, on fourth stump. Smith gets behind the line and blocks it to the off side.
Rabada comes 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball, on off. David Warner tries to drive it away but inside-edges it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, wide outside off. Warner stays back and tries to cut it away. The ball goes back to the bowler off the inner half.
Fraction short, with some width on offer. Warner dabs it through point and crosses for a single. The MCG is on its feet as Warner gets his half-century in his 100th Test match.
Back of a length, around off, climbing on the batter. Steven Smith hangs back and blocks it with straight bat.
This is on a good length and on middle, Steven Smith looks to play at it, but gets squared up and the ball takes an outside edge and goes past the diving gully fielder. Two runs taken!
Back of a length and around off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, David Warner guides it towards point.
Back of a length and around off, David Warner cuts it straight to point again.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a bouncer at 150 clicks, on middle and off, David Warner sways away from it.

FOUR! This is full and outside off, David Warner gets into position early and drives it firmly through covers, but it does not have that much legs in it. Dean Elgar from covers chase and keeps it inside, but the batters run four runs.
Short of a length and on off, David Warner punches it over point for a single.
On a length and on middle, Steven Smith works it towards square leg for a run.
This is on a good length and on off, shaping away, Steven Smith shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it to the right of short leg.
Kagiso Rabada serves this full and on off, Steven Smith prods forward a bit and lets it go to the keeper.
Full again but way outside off, Steven Smith chase it but mistimes his drive towards covers.
FOUR! This is classic Smith! Kagiso Rabada serves this full once more, on off, Steven Smith takes his front foot near the ball and drives it through covers for a beautiful boundary.
Back of a length and outside off, Steven Smith offers no shot at it.
On a length, wide of off. David Warner lets it be.
David Warner blocks this length ball off his front foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! David Warner gets his fifth boundary of the innings. It is much fuller, outside off. Warner looks to drive it away. It takes a thick outside edge and goes past the gully fielder. It races away to the fence.
A single now as this length ball is pushed into covers by the left-hander.
An inswinging delivery, full and on leg. Steven Smith gets inside the line and clips it to the right of mid on. Khaya Zondo is quick to get low to his right and stop the ball.
Good length, around leg. Smith gets pinged on his thigh pads as he decides to leave this delivery.
Marco Jansen starts his spell with a loosener. It is too full, sliding down leg. Warner flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off, defended out.
Way too full and wide outside off, moving further away. Smith leaves it alone.

JUST SHORT! Marco Jansen serves it touch full, outside off. It shapes away a bit off the deck. Steven Smith gets on his front foot and tries to block it out but he only manage to get a thick outside edge. It does not carry to the man at second slip. Smith gets fortunate this time.
Short ball, down leg, left alone.
A short ball, on off. Smith defends it out watchfully. A probing over by Jansen comes to an end here.
A short ball, on off. Warner gets behind and blocks it with a straight bat.
A length ball, around off. Warner blocks it into covers off the front foot.
FOUR! Perfectly placed. It is very full, wide outside off. David Warner gets down on one knee and smashes it through the cover region. It races away to the fence.
Back of a length, wide of off. Warner plays it late and dabs it to deep point for a single. 100 is up for Australia.
A good-length ball, outside off, shapes in a bit later. Steven Smith makes a good leave.
Steven Smith blocks this length ball safely. 5 runs off the over. The bowlers are finding it really hard to cause any trouble here.
Quite full, on fifth stump, it nips away off the deck. David Warner makes a good leave.
A length ball, shaping away from the left-hander. David Warner blocks it out.
Some width on offer as Jansen serves it on a length, wide of off. Warner cuts it towards point and crosses.
Jansen comes 'round the wicket. The seamer angles in a length ball. Smith lets it be.
Much fuller, outside off. Smith across and defends it to cover-point.
Good movement! It is full and wide outside off. The ball swings in a long way off the deck. Steven Smith is not bothered by the movement here and makes a sharp leave.
Good lenght, angled into the pads. Warner nudges it to the leg side.
Back of a length, on fifth stump. This one holds its line. David Warner watches it sail past him.
Fraction short, on top of off. David Warner hops inside the crease and defends it to point for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Lungi Ngidi serves it full, swinging into the pads. Smith flicks it towards mid on.
LEG BYE! Good length, shaping down leg. Smith misses his flick. It brushes the pads and goes down to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Smith clips it to square leg.
A sharp bouncer, wide of off. Smith tries to chase it but misses. This one is just whiskers away from the outside edge.
Jansen bends his back hard and serves a hard length ball, in the channel. Steven Smith lets it be.
Very full, wide of off, swinging in a bit. Smith looks to go for the drive but gets it to the leg side off the inner half.
An in-tucker this time, on a fuller length. Smith shuffles and nudges it to the leg side.
This is outside off and Smith leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, angled in from 'round the wicket, on top of off. Warner opens the face and guides it to the off side.
Much fuller, on off. Warner blocks it with full face.
David Warner drives this full delivery to sweeper cover from outside off. The batters cross for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Smith steps across and punches it to the left of mid off. They take a quick single before the fielder cuts it out.
Full, on fifth stump, left alone.
A length ball, around off. Warner gets it to the man at gully off the outer half.
Quite full, wide of off. Smith tries to drive it through the off side but gets it to square leg off the inside edge. They take one.
Good running! David Warner gets into the 70s. It is very full, on middle and leg. David Warner drives it down the ground towards long on. They take three.

DROPPED! Kyle Verreynne is unable to gather the ball safely and Steven Smith gets another chance at the crease. It is a short ball, angling down leg. Smith goes for the pull but only manages to glove it to the left of the keeper. Kyle Verreynne dives to that side but it spills out of his gloves.
On off, defended out.
Touch short, outside off. Smith leaves it alone.
Good length, on fifth stump. Smith shuffles and blocks it away.
On a length, wide outside off. Warner has no shot to offer.
This is on a good length, with some extra bounce, outside off. Warner leaves it alone.

FOUR! Nothing is going South African's way here. It is a length balll, on off. David Warner gets a thick inside edge as he tries to push it through covers. The ball scoots past the stump and races down to the fine leg fence.
A length ball, outside off. Warner defends it out watchfully.
It is full and on off. Warner pushes it down the ground. Steven Smith tries to get out of the way but gets it to stop instead.
A single now as this is clipped to the leg side.

FOUR RUNS! David Warner becomes only the eighth batsman for Australia to score 8000 runs in this format. He gets soaked with applauds. It is tossed up, full and outside off. David Warner carves it through covers. The fielder makes a solid stop in the deep but the batters run four anyways.
Fuller, wide of off. Warner leans in and drives it through covers for three runs.
On off, defended out.
Pushed through quicker and on off. Smith nudges it to the leg side.
On off, defended out.
On middle and leg, tucked to the leg side.
Back of a length and outside off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Marco Jansen serves this full and on off, Steven Smith goes for the driver but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! This has been put away! Marco Jansen lands this short and on middle, Steven Smith stands tall and pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
A sharp bouncer, on middle, Steven Smith ducks under it.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Smith! This is short and outside off, Steven Smith slices it over point for a boundary.
Short of a length and on off, Steven Smith offers no shot at it.
It is full and outside off. Warner flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
This is pushed through full and on off. Smith pushes it to mid off and crosses.
Flatter one, on the pads. Warner tucks it to the leg side.
Loops it up, full and on off. Warner presses forward and pushes it to cover.
Touch short, Warner goes back and defends it out.
Quicker and full, outside off. Warner blocks it back to the bowler on the front foot.
Jansen comes from 'round the wicket and angles it in on a length, around off. It shapes away a touch off the deck. Smith trie to chase it but gets beaten.
WIDE! Very full. wide outside off. The umpire signals a wide straightaway.
Steven Smith leaves it alone as this is served outside off.

Is it toe first? Dean Elgar seems to be interested and takes a review for lbw. It is a full delivery, angled in on off. Smith tries to dig it out but it gets pinged on his pads first. Later it goes through the off side off his bat and they run two. The review is taken and the Ball Tracking confirms that the impact is outside the line. South Africa lose a review here.
Full and on off, Steven Smith blocks it out.
Nice delivery! This is on a good length and around off, Steven Smith looks to block it out, but the ball just goes past the outside edge towards the keeper.
Back of a length and outside off, Steven Smith shoulders arms to it.
It is full and on off. Warner dances down the track and works it back to the bowler.
On off, defended back to the bowler once again.
Flatter and on off, defended back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out.
Full and on off, driven to long off for a signle.
Loops it up, full and on off. Smith defends it out solidly. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Short of a length and on off, David Warner stays there and blocks it out towards the bowler.
Back of a length and around leg, David Warner pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
This is on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Length again and on off, Steven Smith pushes it towards covers.

FOUR! Just over! Anrich Nortje bowls a good short delivery, on middle at 151 clicks, Steven Smith goes for the pull shot but gets hurried as the ball takes the top edge and flies just over the keeper for a boudnary.
Back of a length and on off, Steven Smith taps it in front of covers for a quick single.
SIX! BANG! Steven Smith goes big now! This is tossed up and around middle, Steven Smith dances down the track and smokes it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
A bit short and on off, Steven Smith defends it on the back foot.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated, short and off, Steven Smith uses his feet and knocks it past silly point.
Shortish and on off, Steven Smith punches it towards covers.
Another dot as this short delievery is blocks it towards silly point.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length at 152 clicks, on off, angling in, David Warner looks to cut it from close to his body but misses.
This is on a hard length and on off, angling in again, David Warner bunts it onto the ground as the ball goes nowehere.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a fiery bouncer now, on middle, David Warner goes for the pull shot but fails to connect.
Back of a length and on middle, David Warner hops up a bit and blocks it to the off side.
Short and outside off, David Warner steers it towards deep point for a single.
Full and on off, Steven Smith defends it towards the short cover region.
Short and on middle, turning in, David Warner blocks it towards short leg.
Short again and around off, David Warner defends it down the pitch.
Slightly shorter and on leg, David Warner nudges it towards short fine leg for a single.
Keshav Maharaj continues with his shorter length, outside off this time, Steven Smith cuts it but finds covers.
Tossed up, full and on off, Steven Smith defends it on the front foot.
Shortish and on middle, Steven Smith keeps it out.
This is on a good length and on middle, angling in, David Warner looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Back of a length and outside off, David Warner slaps it towards deep point for a single. He moves into the 90s now.
Full but down the leg side, Steven Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Short of a length and on leg, Steven Smith gets cramped a bit and helps it towards short fine leg for a run.
Anrich Nortje nails the yorker this time, on off, angling in, David Warner does really well to get his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Back of a length and on middle, David Warner works it through square leg for one.
Floated, full and on off, David Warner uses his feet and drives it towards mid off for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, turning away, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
A bit short and on off, Steven Smith pushes it off the back foot towards covers.
Quicker one, full and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it down the pitch.
Gives this one some air, on off, Steven Smith leans on and defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery, full and on middle, Steven Smith is solid in his defense again.
On a length and on off, David Warner cuts it towards point.
Goes fuller this time and outside off, David Warner mistimes his drive towards mid off.

FOUR BYES! Anrich Nortje bangs in bouncer on middle, takes off from the surface, David Warner ducks under it and Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps fails to reach it with his leap as the ball races towards the fence for a boundary.
Quickest delivery of the match so far! This is full and on middle at 155 clicks, David Warner knocks it with the inner half towards mid on.
Short of a length and on leg, David Warner turns it towards square leg for a single.
Another good bouncer, on middle and leg, Steven Smith ducks underneath it.
Tossed up, full and on middle, David Warner goes down and sweeps it wide of deep square leg for a brace. He moves to 95!
Short and on middle, David Warner defends it on the back foot.
Floated, short and on off, David Warner blocks it out.
Flatter, full and on middle, David Warner knocks back to the bowler.
Looped up, on leg, David Warner comes down the track and drills it towards long on for a run.
A bit short and on off, Steven Smith moves back and pushes it towards covers.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR WARNER! He marks his 100th Test with a ton. He certainly needed this knock to boost his confidence after a lean patch in the recent years. Kagiso Rabada lands this short and down the leg, David Warner pulls it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. He celebrates the moment by taking off his helmet and acknowledges the crowd.
Full and on leg, David Warner flicks it through square leg for a single.
This is on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Goes fuller and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it out.
On a length and on middle, Steven Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Length again and on middle, Steven Smith defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is floated, full and on middle, David Warner goes down and whips it away towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Short and on middle, David Warner tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Steven Smith uses his feet and turns this short delivery towards mid-wicket for no run.
Tossed up, full and on off, Steven Smith blocks it out.
Slower through the air, on off, Steven Smith opens the face of his bat and guides it towards point.
Flatter, on middle, Steven Smith stays back and defends it again.
It is on a fuller length, on middle and leg. Warner goes back and flicks it through mid-wicket for three runs. The stand moves to 100 runs.
Steven Smith flicks it off his hips to mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Warner blocks it out solidly.
A length ball, sliding down leg. Warner tries to pull it away but drags it to the right of the keeper. Kyle Verreynne is quick to slide to his right and make a sharp stop.
Full and on off, defended out.
A length ball, angled in from outside off. David Warner blocks it off his back foot.
Loops it full and on off. Smith strokes it down to long off for an easy single.
David Warner gets down on one knee for this full delivery and reverse sweeps it to past point for a couple.
On off, blocked out.
It is full and on off. Warner presses forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
This is down leg. Warner sweeps it to short fine.
Flatter one, on leg. David Warner stays back and flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. David Warner swivels and pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
This is sliding down leg, Smith lets it be.
On a good length, outside off. It climbs on the batter. Steven Smith tries to punch it through the line but it dies in front of him off the inside edge.
Length, on top of off. Smith keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it with a straight bat.
Touch fuller, shaping into the batter, on leg. Smith shuffles a bit and flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Warner punches this length ball to point. There is a misfield which allows the batter to take a single.
Keshav Maharaj drags his length back, on leg. David Warner flicks it through square leg and crosses.
Tosses it up, around off. Steven Smith gets forward and blocks it out.
Much fuller and on leg. Steven Smith flicks it aerially over mid-wicket. Anrich Nortje gives it a long chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off. David Warner defends it out watchfully.
Loops it up, full and on off. Warner blocks it on his front foot.

NO BALL! The South African celebrations have been cut short here as Kagiso Rabada oversteps. Although, it could've been ruled out soon after if it was not for the no ball, as Steven Smith was sure that he got pinged on his arms rather than gloving it. Coming to the delivery. It is a short ball, on middle and leg. Smith goes for the pull but is a touch early into his shot. The ball lobs off his back hand and Kyle Verreynne gathers it safely. Kagiso Rabada appeals and the umpire his finger after giving it some thought. Steven Smith signals for a review straightaway but it is not required as the umpire signals a no ball for overstepping.
Full and on off. Smith drives it straight down the ground for three runs.
This is on a good length and on middle, David Warner knocks it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller this time, on off, slower too, David Warner drives it through covers for a single.
Short and on middle, Steven Smith pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Another short delivery, on off, David Warner pulls it through mid-wicket for one. Australia lead by 5 runs now.
Kagiso Rabada bangs in a bouncer, on off, Steven Smith sways away from it.
Tosses it up and full. David Warner flicks it down to long on from outside off, He crosses for one.

Lands short! It is looped up, full and on off. It grips and turns away a touch. Smith dances down the track and looks to flick it across the line. The ball takes the outside edge but lands short of the man at gully.
A single now as this is eased down to long off.
On off, defended out.
Attacking the stumps with a length ball, Warner hangs back and blocks it away.
This is straying on the pads. Warner goes back and clips it to the leg side for a single now.
A length ball, shaping down leg. Warner does not bother.
Full length, wide of off. Warner drives it to covers but not in the gap.
Good length, outside off. Warner shuffles and defends it out watchfully.
David Warner cuts this short ball towards deep point. They take a single.
This is on a length, outside off, nips in off the deck. Steven Smith defends it out.
LEG BYE! Very full, shaping down leg. Smith misses his flick. It brushes his pads and rolls down to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Smith knocks it down to long on for one.
This one turns in from outside off to hit Warner high on his pads as he comes down the track to block it away.
Touch short, on off. Warner flicks it to mid-wicket.
Warner flicks it to square leg off his hips for a single.
On middle and leg, Smith defends it into the deck.
Pushed through quicker and fuller, on off. Smith blocks into covers on his front foot.
Full length, on fourth stump. Warner opens the face and pushes it to cover.
A low full toss, angled across the left-hander, outside off. Warner works it to the man at point.

OH NO! Kyle Verreynne has his hands on his head as he remains on the floor. It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Warner looks to flick it away but misses. It goes off his thigh pads to the right of the keeper. Kyle Verreynne dives to that side but it comes off his gloves. The ball is about to hit the helmet placed behind him but a fielder comes in quickly and collects it. Although, the replays later confirm that there is no bat on it. Kyle Verreynne shouldn't be gutted anymore.
Length, on off, defended out.
A length ball, right in the channel. Warner gets behind and defends it away.
David Warner flicks this good-length delivery off his hips to square leg for one.
It is short, turning into the batter. David Warner stays back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. They take a couple.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
David Warner comes down the track and defends this full delivery to short mid on.
