This is full and on leg. Warner sweeps it towards square leg. Lungi Ngidi dives to his right and stop the ball with one hand. It looks like Warner might've hurt himself by getting back up here.
Flatter and on off. Warner pats it back to the bowler.
On middle and leg, flicked to square leg.
Jansen dishes it full, outside off. Smith drives it on the up but straight to the man at covers.
Marco Jansen serves this one on a length, wide of off from 'round the wicket. Smith lets it be.
This one is angled into the pads. Smith tucks it behind square on the leg side for one.
A short ball, sliding down leg. Warner drags his pull to short fine.
Length ball, outside off. Warner eases it to point for a quick single.
FOUR! Steven Smith brings up his half-century in fine fashion. It is a short ball, wide outside off. Steven Smith rides the bounce and cuts it along the ground through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Fine shot! This is tossed up, full and on middle, David Warner goes down and slog-sweeps it towards the vacant deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Floated, short and on middle, David Warner blocks it out.
Quicker one, full and on middle, David Warner defends it on the front foot.
A bit short and around off, David Warner stays back and keeps it away.
Flighted delivery, full and on off, David Warner guides it towards point for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Steven Smith goes down and scoops it towards fine leg for a run.
This is on a good length and on off, Steven Smith pushes it towards covers.
Goes short and on middle, Steven Smith pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and on middle, David Warner knocks it towards mid on.
Marco Jansen bowls this on a hard length and on leg, angling in, David Warner misses his flick as the ball loops up off his pads into the hands of gully.
Fuller one and on middle, David Warner drives it towards mid off for a run. Oh..no! It is called a no ball for overstepping.
Fuller again and on off, Steven Smith defends it to the off side.
Short and on off this time, Steven Smith pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Floated and around middle, David Warner uses his feet and blocks it down the pitch.
Short and on middle, David Warner forces it through square leg for one.
Fires in a yorker now, on middle, Steven Smith digs it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, full and on off, Steven Smith leans on and blocks it out.
Looped up, full and on off, Steven Smith drives it towards long off for a run.
Shorter in length and on off, David Warner mistimes his cut back towards the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, Steven Smith punches it towards covers.
This is on a good length and around off, Steven Smith lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on middle, Steven Smith drives it straight to mid on.
Full again and on off, Steven Smith drills it towards covers where the fielder parries it to mid off. They cross.
Marco Jansen lands this short and on middle, David Warner pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one. That brings up the 150-run partnership between these two batters.
Short again and on middle, Steven Smith pulls it through square leg for one more.
Floated, full and on off, Steven Smith eases it towards long off for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, David Warner blocks it out.
Flatter and around middle, David Warner uses his feet and works it towards mid-wicket.
Short and on off, David Warner pushes it towards wide of covers for a run.
On off, kept out.
A bit short and on off, Steven Smith moves back and punches it towards point.
Short of a length and on middle, David Warner swats it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Steven Smith blocks it to the off side.
A good bouncer now, on middle, Steven Smith ducks under it.
Full but down the leg this time, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Length again and on off, Steven Smith pushes it towards covers.
A slower one now, full and on middle, Steven Smith works it with the inner half through square leg for a brace. That will be TEA ON DAY 2!
Floated, short and on leg, David Warner flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Short and outside off, Steven Smith cuts it towards point and sets off for the run. The fielder there hits the stumps a the batter's end but Warner is in.
Short again and on off, David Warner punches it towards covers.
Tossed up, full and on off, David Warner pushes it towards covers.
Looped up, full and on off, David Warner guides it with the outer half through point for one.
Flatter, full and on off, Steven Smith drives it towards short covers.
A full toss, on off, David Warner drills it straigh to short covers.
Back of a length and on leg, David Warner helps it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! In the gap! This is short and on middle, Steven Smith swivels and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boudnary.
This is on a hard length and on middle, Steven Smith looks to play at it, but the extra bounce takes the ball past his bat and he gets hit on his thumb.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith waits for it and steers it past short third man for a boundary.
Full and on off, Steven Smith drives it towards mid off.
Short and on middle, David Warner flicks it off the back foot through square leg for a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it out.
Floated and around off, Steven Smith defends it to the off side.
On middle, blocked out.
Shortish and on off, Steven Smith strides forward and pushes it towards covers.
Darts this one full and on off, Steven Smith drives it towards short covers.
FOUR! Deft touch! This is on a hard length and outside off, David Warner stays there and just guides it wide of third man for a boundary.
A slower delievry again, on a length and on middle, angling in, David Warner gets cramped and keeps it out to the leg side.
Full and on middle, David Warner tucks it towards deep square leg for a run.
FOUR! Great shot! Lungi Ngidi lands this short and on middle, Steven Smith stays there and pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, Steven Smith knocks it towards mid on.
Length again and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it to the leg side.
Short and outside off, David Warner cuts it uppishly but wide of short cover for a brace.
Short again and on middle, David Warner forces it towards wide of long on for a couple of runs.
Floated, full and on middle, David Warner blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and on off, David Warner defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Good shot! This is flighted, full and on middle, David Warner goes down and heaves it towards the deep mid-wicket fence where the fielder tries to keep it in but fails to do so. 150 up for David Warner!
Fires this one full and on the pads, David Warner tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Kagiso Rabada bowls this short and outside off, David Warner frees his arms and punches it past covers for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner cuts it towards sweeper cover for a single.
This is on a good length and around off, Steven Smith lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Steven Smith gets into the act now! This is short and on middle, Steven Smith picks up the length early and pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Short again and on middle, Steven Smith pulls it wide of deep square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner punches it though point for run.
Tossed up, on middle, David Warner comes down the track and drives it towards long on for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Steven Smith blocks it out.
On middle, blocked out.
A bit short and on middle, Steven Smith defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Steven Smith knocks it back to the bowler.
This is almost on a yorker length and on middle, Steven Smith jams it out towards long on for a run. 200-run partnership comes up with that between these two batters.
On a length and on off, Steven Smith leaves it alone. It is called a no ball for overstepping.
Full and on off, Steven Smith drives it through covers for a run.
Short of a length and on middle, David Warner looks to pull it away, but gets hurried as the ball hits him on the stomach area.
FOUR! Up and over! This is full and on middle, David Warner stays there and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner dabs it towards point.
Full and on middle, David Warner chips it in the air, but it lands safely behind mid on as the batters complete two runs.
Short and on middle, David Warner pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
SIX! BOOM! David Warner is in the mood here! This is tossed up, full and on middle, David Warner goes down and slog-sweeps it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short adn on middle, David Warner pulls it through square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Steven Smith lobs it in front of deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Flatter, full and on leg, Steven Smith goes down and paddles it towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Steven Smith leans on and defends.
Shortish and on middle, Steven Smith nudges it towards mid-wicket.
This is on a hard length and on middle, angling in, David Warner misses and gets hit on his pads.

Short of a length and on middle, David Warner looks to pull it away, but misses as the ball brushes off the pads and goes through to the keeper. There is an appeal for caught behind but turned down. South Africa take the review but is wasted as replays confirms no bat involved.
Short again and on middle, David Warner pulls it wide of deep square leg for a brace.
A slower one, on a length and on off, David Warner pushes it through cover-point for a single.
Full and on off, Steven Smith blocks it out to the off side.
Back of a length and on off, Steven Smith steers it towards gully.
FOUR! Powered away! This is tossed up, full and on off, David Warner thrashes it wide of mid off for a boundary.
SIX! Up, up and away! This is floated, full and on off, David Warner launches it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short and on middle, David Warner pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted and on middle, Steven Smith uses his feet and forces it towards long on for a run.
Slightly shorter and on off, David Warner carves it through covers for a brace. He moves into 190s now.
Short again and outside off, David Warner punches it through covers for a couple of runs.

OUT! TAKEN! Anrich Nortje strikes right after drinks! South Africa finally breaks this partnership and there is a sense of relief among their players. Anrich Nortje bowls this short of a length and on off, Steven Smith looks to upper cut it, but the ball keeps a bit low and takes the bottom edge to go straight into the Theunis de Bruyn at gully who makes no mistake. Steven Smith is really disappointed with himself as he departs on 85. Australia lose their third.
Howout: c Theunis de Bruyn b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Back of a length and on leg, Travis Head nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, David Warner backs away and goes for the cut, but misses.
Short of a length and on middle, angling in, David Warner knocks it towards mid on.
Length again and on off, David Warner punches it towards covers where the fielder makes a half-stop. They cross.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, Travis Head ducks under it.
Tossed up, full and on middle, David Warner reverse-sweeps it towards point for a single.
Short and on middle, turning in, Travis Head moves back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Short again and on leg, Travis Head flicks it through square leg for one.
Another short delivery, on middle, David Warner goes for the pull shot, but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Quicker, full and on middle, David Warner drills it back to the bowler.
A bit short and around leg, David Warner works it towards square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, David Warner blocks it out down the pitch.
Fuller and on off, David Warner drives it straight to covers.
Short and way outside off, David Warner reaches for it and taps it through point for a run.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is back of a length and on off, Travis Head stays there and punches it from the middle of the bat towards the deep point fence for a boundary.
Full and on the pads, Travis Head tucks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.

EDGE AND FOUR! DOUBLE HUNDRED FOR WARNER! Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length and on off, David Warner looks to push it away, but gets an outside edge past slip cordon for a boundary. He becomes the first Australian player to score a double-ton on their 100th Test match. He still has some energy left for his trademark celebratin and he soaks in all the applause. This has been a fine effort from him and he has written history here. A day to remember for Warner!
Tossed up, full and on off, Travis Head drives it towards short covers.
Short and on leg, Travis Head tucks it towards square leg.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated, full and on middle, Travis Head looks to drive it but gets an outside edge towards point for a single.
Quicker, full and on middle, Cameron Green knocks it back to the bowler.
Another dot as this full delivery is driven back to the bowler.
FOUR! A poor delivery and rightly punished! This is short and outside off, Travis Head slices it over point for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! This is back of a length and outside off, Travis Head punches it in front of square on the off side for a boundary.

Full and on middle, Travis Head drives it back to the bowler where Lungi Ngidi picks it up and throws at the batter's end where the ball hits the bat of Head as he tries to get away from the line of the ball.
Full again and on off, Travis Head mistimes his drive towards the bowler.
On a length and around leg, Travis Head helps it towards fine leg for a single.
Length again and on off, angling in, Cameron Green blocks it out.
Angles this into the batter, short and on leg, Travis Head works it towards square leg.
Floated, full and on off, Travis Head uses his feet and strokes it towards mid off.
Shortish and on middle, Travis Head tucks it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Another boudnary for Head! This is short again and outside off, Travis Head moves back and slaps it towards the deep point fence where Anrich Nortje tries his best running from his left, but fails to stop the boundary.
Flatter, full and on middle, Travis Head eases it towards long on for a run.
Short and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it out.
Anrich Nortje starts with a sharp bouncer on middle. Head ducks under it.
A length ball, around off. Head hangs back and defends it out.
A length ball, wide of off. Head dabs it down to third man for one.
BEATEN! A length ball, in the channel. Green hangs his blade away from the body to get beaten on the outside edge.
This is outside off, left alone.
Green serves it on a length, wide of off. Green has no shot to offer.
Jansen dishes a length ball, outside off. Head lets it be.
SIX! All the way! It is too full and straight attacking the pads. Travis Head stays back and powers it over the square leg fence for a biggie. Wonderful use of the wrists this time.
A length ball, wide outside off, shaping away a touch. Head looks to block it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This is a length ball, outside off. Head leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full and on off. Head blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Travis Head is on a roll here. It is full and on middle. Head flicks it aerially towards the cow corner. It goes for four runs.
This one shapes in from outside off, on a good length. Green offers full face of the blade.
Overpitched, outside off. Green steps across and strokes it into covers.
Anrich Nortje fires in a yorker, in the blockhole, at around 144 km/h. Green stays back and digs it out right in time.
A well-directed short ball, on the bodyline. It climb onto the batter. Green lobs it behind short leg, who is unable to get to the ball in time. It lands safely as it lobs of his blade.
On off, defended out. Green is yet to get off the mark here.
Green is finally off the mark now! It is full, on middle and leg. Green stays back and flicks it to deep mid-wicket. They take two as there is protection in the deep.
A length ball, angled down leg. Head stays back and clips it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, angling away. Green lets it be.
Fraction short, in the channel, swinging in a touch late. Green shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, angled across, outside off. Green taps it into covers.
A length ball, wide of off. Green looks to play at it but misses.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! It is full, around off. Green steps forward and drives it down the ground for a boundary at long off.
This is a good-length delivery, on top of off. Head stays back and deals with it.
Full, on the pads, Head flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Green tucks this length ball, off his hips, towards the man at short leg.

A short ball, coming into the batter, from outside off. It gets big on the batter. Green hops inside his crease, closes the face and blocks it to the leg side, although off his gloves, as he gets hit hard on his right hand, on the top of the blade.
It is a half-volley, around off. Carey drives it down the ground. The batters take two runs before the fielder cuts it out.
It is a short ball, angled down leg. Carey looks to heave it across the line but it lobs off the top-edge and lands in front of him.
Jansen starts with a full one, sliding down leg. Head misses his flick.
A short ball, on off. Head hops and blocks it to the off side.
On  a length, on top of off. Head opens the face and dabs it down past backward point for a single.
This is full and outside off. Carey leans in and drives it into covers.
Fraction short, on off. Carey taps it to point.
Much fuller, outside off, shaping in a touch. Carey pushes it to the man at mid off. Just a single off the over then.
A short ball, on leg. Head stays back and tries to flick it away. The ball goes to square leg off his thigh pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Length and on off, blocked out,
This is full, on middle and leg. Carey clips it to the leg side.
Anrich Nortje cuts the batter in half now. It is quite short, on middle. Carey hops inside the crease and tries to flick it away but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Good length, around off. Carey defends it into covers.
Anrich Nortje dishes a short ball, on top of off. Carey stays back and fends it out.
Full and on off, blocked back to the bowler.
A short ball, in the channel of uncertainty. Head leaves it alone for the keeper.
Back of a length, wide of off. Head latches onto it and cuts it through covers. They take a single.
This is outside off, left alone by Carey.
It is a short ball, outside off. a bit close to the batter. Carey looks to go for the cut shot but misses it completely.
Bangs it in short, wide outside off. Carey lets it be.
A length ball, outside off. Head reaches out and hammers it through the gap at covers. Dean Elgar gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
A length ball, on middle. Carey tucks it to the leg side.
Alex Carey steps across to this length ball and blocks it out watchfully.
Much fuller, on off stump. Carey pushes it towards mid off with full face of the blade.
A length ball, around off. Carey looks to punch it away. It goes to the leg side off the inside edge. They take a quick single.
A short ball, on middle. This one gets bigger on the batsman. Head hops inside the crease with his blade near his face. It pops up but lands safely on the leg side.
Length, angled across the left-hander. Carey taps it through covers for a single.
Tossed up, on off, defended on the front foot.
Head presses forward and blocks this full delivery back to the bowler.
Short, on fourth stump. Head pushes it out.
Fuller, wide of off. Head knocks it to long off.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is full, and down leg. Head gets low and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. He moves to 44 now.
FOUR! Find the gap really well. It is overpitched, outside off. Carey shuffles and carves it through the gap at covers for four runs. This is a good-looking shot.
Full and on the stumps. Carey drives it down the ground. Kagiso Rabada makes a solid stop with his feet.
On off, pushed into covers.
On the pads, Carey stays back and clips it to deep square leg. They cross for one.
On a length, on middle and leg, this one stays low. Head tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! It is a length ball, down leg. Head stays back and glances it around the corner. It races away to the fine leg fence. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Anrich Nortje start with a full delivery on leg, Alex Carey flicks it through square leg for a single.
Sharp bouncer! Anrich Nortje bangs this short and on middle, Travis Head gets hurried but does well to duck under it.
Goes fuller and on middle, Travis Head knocks it towards mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Travis Head blocks it in front of short covers.
Back of a length and around off, Travis Head cuts it towards deep point for a run.
Length again and on leg, Alex Carey nudges it towards fine leg for one.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a full delivery as well and around off, angling away, Alex Carey looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full again and on off, Alex Carey drives it towards covers.
FOUR! Nice timing! Kagiso Rabada bowls this back of a length and on off, Alex Carey stays there and punches it wide of deep point for a boundary.
Fuller one and on off, Alex Carey pushes it towards covers.
On a length and on off, Alex Carey defends it towards mid off.
Another dot as this full delivery is knocked towards covers.
This is on a good length and on leg, Travis Head looks to work it away but gets a leading edge down the pitch.
FIFTY FOR HEAD! He is having a great time out there and has continued his good form.This is short and on middle, Travis Head pulls it towards deep square leg for a brace.

OUT! TIMBER! Anrich Nortje strikes in his second over! Travis Head goes back to the hut just after his half-century. Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and around leg, Travis Head looks to flick it away, but the ball skids through the surface and brushes off the pads to rattle the stumps. South Africa get the much-needed breakthrough.
Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED UP! Anrich Nortje with the double whammy! He is on a hat-trick now! David Warner came out to face just one ball here and his innings end on 200. Anrich Nortje goes for the yorker, but bowls a low full toss, on leg, David Warner looks to dig it out, but plays down the wrong line and the ball deflects off his pads to shatter the stumps again. David Warner make the walk back to a standing ovation. Australia five down now!
Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: No hat-trick for Anrich Nortje! This is full and on leg, Pat Cummins manages to block it out towards point with the outer half of the bat.
FOUR! Pat Cummins gets off the mark! Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and on off, Pat Cummins guides it behind point for a boundary.
Full and on off, Alex Carey drives it towards deep point for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada strikes now! South Africa take a good review here and Pat Cummins becomes the latest victim. Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and on the fifth stump line, Pat Cummins looks to block it out, but gets the slightest of outside edges through to the keeper where Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake. There is an appeal for the catch but the finger stays down. However, Dean Elgar goes for the review where there is nothing on the Hotspot but Snicko shows a spike when the ball passes the bat. The onfield decison is changed and Australia lose their sixth.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Rabada goes full and sliding down leg. Lyon tries to flick it away but misses.
FOUR! Up and over! A length ball, outside off. Lyon tries to punch it through the off side. The ball takes the outside edge and flies over the slip cordon. Four runs.
Back of a length, wide of off. Lyon looks to chase it but misses.
Swing and a miss! Good length, wide of off. Lyon slashes and misses.
On off, pushed away.
Full and on off, Alex Carey drives it straight to short covers.
Anrich Nortje bowls this with a scrambled seam, on a good length and on off, angling away, Alex Carey looks to push it away, but gets beaten as the keeper collects it on the bounce.
Back of a length and on middle, Alex Carey knocks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Fine shot! This is full and around off, Alex Carey stays there and thrashes it through covers for a boundary.
Full and on leg, Alex Carey drives it wide of mid on for a single.
This is on a good length and on leg, Alex Carey blocks it out to the leg side.
Oh..that is close! Kagiso Rabada bowls this a bit fuller and on off, Alex Carey looks to play at it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. It could have easily gone onto the stumps.
Short and on middle, Alex Carey pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! This is on a hard length and on leg, Nathan Lyon whips it towards the vacant deep sqaure leg fence for a boundary.
Full and on middle, Nathan Lyon chips it over mid on for brace.
On a length and on middle, Nathan Lyon blocks it to the leg side.
Full and on off, Alex Carey drives it towards short covers.
Pulls his length back a bit, on leg, Alex Carey looks to flick it but misses as the ball goes off his pads to the right of the keeper.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is full again and around fof, Alex Carey reaches for it a bit and slaps it towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Another full delivery, on off, Alex Carey drills it towards mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Alex Carey defends it towards covers.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a short delivery, on middle and off, Alex Carey tries to make room and upper cut it, but misses it completely.
Full and down the leg, Nathan Lyon misses his flick as the ball deflects off his pads towards the keeper where Kyle Verreynne dives to his left to make a good half-stop.
Back of a length and on off, Nathan Lyon mistimes his cut towards point.
Fuller one and on middle, Nathan Lyon lobs it over mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Swing and a miss! This is on a good length and on middle, Nathan Lyon goes for the big heave, but misses as the ball just goes over the stumps through to the keeper.
Kagiso Rabada lands this short and on middle, Nathan Lyon is through his pull shot way too early and toe-ends it to the off side.
SIX! BANG! Nathan Lyon connects this time alright! This is short again and around leg, Nathan Lyon swivels and hooks it over the fine leg fence for a biggie.
Marco Jansen starts with full delivery but down the leg side, Alex Carey misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads towards the keeper where Kyle Verreynne collects it diving to his right.
Full again and on middle, Alex Carey knocks it towards mid on.
On a length and on leg, Alex Carey nudges it towards fine leg but denies for the run.
Short of a length and outside off, Alex Carey lets it go to the keeper.
Goes fuller and on leg, Alex Carey tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Good placement! Marco Jansen bowls this short of a length and outside off, Alex Carey bends down a bit and upper cuts it towards the vacant third man fence for a boundary.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a full delivery, on middle, Nathan Lyon goes for the drive, but gets an inside edge onto his pads. It was curtains for him if he missed that.
Full again and on off, Nathan Lyon this time times his drive well towards the long off region for three runs.
Back of a length and on middle, Alex Carey blocks it down the pitch.
Good fielding! This is full and on off, Alex Carey drives it wide of mid off where Kagiso Rabada puts in a brilliant dive to his right to stop it. They cross.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! This is full and on off, Nathan Lyon prods forward and gently pushes it away through extra covers for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Nathan Lyon's nice little cameo comes to an end. Lungi Ngidi bangs this short and on middle, Nathan Lyon goes for the pull shot, but gets hurried and mistimes it in the air towards mid-wicket where Khaya Zondo pouches it safely. Australia seven down now.
Howout: c Khaya Zondo b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: FOUR! Down the ground. It is full and on off. Carey drives it down the ground and gets a boundary to long on.
Length, on off, defended into covers.
Fuller, sliding down leg. Carey flicks it behind square on the leg side for one.
Good length, in the channel. It climbs onto the batter. Green hangs his blade away only to get beaten on the outside edge.
A short ball, outside leg. Cameron Green gets inside the line and leaves it alone.
Three dots to end the over! It is a length ball, around off. Green knocks it into covers.
Quite full and on off. Carey plays it back to the bowler.
Goes full again, angled across the left-hander. Carey steps across and pushes it to covers with soft hands.
It is full, attacking the stumps. Carey gets it to the leg side off the inner half as he tries to stroke it through the line.
Good length, on the pads, Carey goes back and clips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Green gets on his front foot for this full delivery and blocks it out.
It is short outside off, niping in a touch. Green shuffles and tucks it to mid-wicket off his hips.
Around off, blocked out.
Jansen goes full, attacking the pads. Carey tickles it to fine leg and crosses for a single.
A short ball, swinging in from outside off. Green mmisses his flick. It goes to Khaya Zondo off the thigh pads.
Length, outside off, pushed out to safety.
A sharp bouncer down leg, Green ducks under it.
Jansen angles it in, full and on off. Green defends it out watchfully.
FOUR! Top shot! 450 is up for the hosts now. It is full and outside off. Alex Carey finds the gap and drives it past mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries. It is short and on off. Alex Carey rides the bounce well and pulls it over mid-wicket for four runs.
FOUR! Three on the trot! He gets to his FIFTY in fine fashion. It is full, attacking the stumps. Alex Carey presses forward and strokes it down the ground for a boundary.
Alex Carey pulls this short ball to deep mid-wicket for a single. The lead moves to 271 runs.
Full and on off. Cameron Green blocks it back to Ngidi.
This is down leg, on the shorter side. Green lets it be.
Fuller, on off. Carey eases it back to the bowler.
Good length, angled across the left-hander. Alex Carey hops and punches it to the right of covers. Temba Bavuma there dives to his right to make a half-stop.
Alex Carey pulls this short ball from outside off towards mid on. A single is taken.
A sharp bouncer, shaping down leg. Green gets inside the line and leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, no shot to offer.
It is full, wide of off. Green drives it to point off the outer half but straight to Rabada.
This is a length ball, straying on the pads, Carey clips it to deep square leg and crosses.
This is short, on top of off. Green stands tall and blocks it into the deck.
A length ball, outside off, this one stays low after hitting the deck. Green leaves it alone.
Cameron Green stands tall to this good-length delivery and defends it out watchfully.
This one pitches outside off but nips in off the deck. Green goes back and blocks it to mid-wicket.
Good running! It is full, on the stumps. Cameron Green leans forward and drives it down the ground towards long off. They take three runs.
Length, on off, blocked out.
Jansen goes short, down leg. Green tries to pull it away. The ball hits him on his gloves and goes behind square on the leg side. One taken.
A sharp bouncer, on leg. Carey leaves it alone.
Alex Carey gets a single as he flicks this full delivery to mid-wicket.
Short ball, around off. Green gets behind and blocks it with a straight bat.
This is angled across, on a fuller length. Green drives it to mid off.
Anrich Nortje goes full, on the pads. Carey stays back and clips it to square leg for a single.
An attempted yorker which turns into a low full toss. Green is able to get it through covers and take a couple.
Good length, it comes in from outside off. Green shuffles and tucks it to the leg side.
Green leaves this bouncer alone.
Three dots now! It is a length ball, around off, angled across. Green shuffles and blocks it with full face.
Quite short, on leg, worked to the leg side off the inner half.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Carey drags his reverse sweep to the first slip.
This is full and on middle. Carey sweeps this behind square on the leg side. One taken.
Green blocks it back to the bowler on the front foot.
Flatter, around middle. Green easesit to mid on for one.
Alex Carey reverse sweeps this length balll, through backward point for a single.
On off, defended out.
It is full, on off stump. Carey pushes it back to the bowler.
Anrich Nortje goes full, angling across the left-hander. Alex Carey gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Good length, down leg. Carey flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
This is short, around the hips. Green tucks it to square leg and crosses.
Alex Carey gets on his front foot for this full delivery and knocks it past the mid of fielder. They take three before Kagiso Rabada chases it down.
Short and on off, defended out.
Floated, full and on middle, Alex Carey tuns it towards short mid-wicket.
A bit short and on middle, Alex Carey uses his feet and tucks through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Cameron Green pushes it towards mid off.
Shortish and on off, Cameron Green punches it towards short mid off.
On middle, blocked out.
Another dot! This is flatter, full and on middle, Cameron Green defends it down the pitch. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Kagiso Rabada begins with a full delivery, on off, Alex Carey works it with the inner half towards mid-wicket for a single.
This is full and on off, swinging away, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
On a length and around leg, Cameron Green tucks it through square leg for a run.
Length again and on off, Alex Carey taps it towards point.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Alex Carey looks to drive it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the all rolls towards the keeper.
This is pitched up, on off, Alex Carey drives it straight to mid off.
Quicker, full and on middle, Cameron Green knocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it out.
Darts this one full and on middle, Cameron Green digs it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on middle, Cameron Green is solid in his defense again.
On middle, blocked out.
A maiden over! This is flighted and around leg, Cameron Green leans on and keeps it out to the leg side.
Short and on middle, Alex Carey pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length and on leg, Cameron Green flicks it through square leg for a brace.
This is on a good length and outside off, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Length again and on middle, angling in, Cameron Green knocks it towards mid on.
Fuller one and outside off, Cameron Green offers no shot at it.
Back of a length and on off, Cameron Green taps it in front of point.
Floated and around middle, Alex Carey blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Alex Carey looks to reverse sweep but gets an inner edge towards slip.
Shortish and on off, Alex Carey pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
Short again and on middle, Alex Carey turns it to the leg side.
A single now as this short delivery is punched towards long on.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cameron Green defends it on the front foot.
This is on a good length and on middle, Alex Carey works it to the leg side.
Length again and on off, Alex Carey defends it towards short covers.
A bit fuller and around leg, Alex Carey clips it towards mid on.
FOUR! Alex Carey finds the fence! This is fuller and on off, slower too, Alex Carey waits for it and lofts it towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Alex Carey dabs it to the off side.
Alex Carey blocks this short-of-a-length delivery towards covers.
Shorter in length and on off, Cameron Green moves back and punches it towards covers.
Floated, full and on middle, Cameron Green drills it back towards the bowler.
Flighted, full and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it with the inner half to the leg side.
Quicker one, full and on middle, Cameron Green eases it towards long on for a run.
Slighlty shorter and on off, Alex Carey defends it off the back foot.
Gives this one some air, on middle, Alex Carey uses his feet and works it towards long on for one.
Short and on middle, Alex Carey pulls it wide of mid on for a single.
Full and on off, Cameron Green pushes it towards mid off.
Full again and on middle, Cameron Green defends it as the ball rolls towards mid off.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and on off, shaping away a bit, Cameron Green guides it towards gully.
This is short and on off, Cameron Green mistimes his pull shot wide of mid-wicket for a couple of ends.
Kagiso Rabada lands this short again and on middle, Cameron Green tries for the pull shot but cue-ends it to the off side.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Alex Carey reverse sweeps it towards deep point for a single.
Short and on off, Cameron Green moves back and slaps it past mid off for a brace.
Floated, full and on middle, Cameron Green drives it back to the bowler.
Flighted, short and on off, turning away, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Looped up, full and on off, Cameron Green prods forward and pushes it towards covers.
Flatter, full and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it down th pitch.
Back of a length and on off, Alex Carey punches it through point for a single.
Short of a length and on middle, Cameron Green tucks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
EDGED AND FOUR! Kagiso Rabada bangs this short and on leg, Alex Carey goes for the pull shot, but gets hurried a bit and top edges it towards the fine leg fence for a boudnary. 500 up for Australia!
FOUR! Deft touch!
This is on a hard length and on leg, Alex Carey looks to play at it, but misses and gets hit on the pads as the ball rolls towards point. There is a stiffled appeal for and LBW, but turned down.
On a length and on middle, Alex Carey knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off, Cameron Green strides forwards and blocks it out.
Shortish and on off, Cameron Green cuts it straight to covers.
On off, kept out.
Floated, full and on off, Cameron Green drives it past short covers and towards long off for a single.
Flighted, full and on middle, Alex Carey uses his feet and turns it towards mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, on off, Alex Carey gets to the pitch of it and pushes it towards mid off.

FOUR! Edgy! It is a length ball, outside off, shaping away a touch. Cameron Green looks to drive it away but gets a thick outside edge. The ball beats the diving fielder at gully and goes down to the fence.
Fuller, on off, blocked on the front foot.
On off, defended out.
It is overpitched, on off. Green knocks it to mid off.
On a good length, wide of off, nips in a touch. Cameron Green shoulders his arms at it.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Green ducks under it wisely.
Alex Carey reverse sweeps this full delivery behind point for an easy single.
This is full, on middle and leg. Green prods forward and blocks it out.
Full and on off. Green drives it towards wide long off and gets a single.
Loops it up, around leg, clipped to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off. Carey reverse-sweeps it towards point for one run.
On off, defended out on the front foot.
A length ball, at 126 clicks, outside off. This one stays low off the deck. Carey flicks it to the leg side.
On a good length, wide of off. Carey plays it late and works it past the man at gully. They take a couple.
This length ball is punched through covers for a run now.
It is fuller, sliding down leg. Green tries to flick but misses.
Full and on off, blocked on the front foot.
A length ball, around off. Green defends it to the off side off the outer half.
This is on leg, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off. Carey reverse sweeps it to deep point and rotates the strike.
Around off, defended out.
Green presses forward and blocks this full delivery into the deck.
Looped up, on off, Green remains solid in his defense.
Full and straight, blocked out solidly.
FOUR! Good use of the wrists. It is a short ball, angling down leg. Alex Carey stays back and pulls it behind square on the leg side. He gets it through the gap and finds a boundary.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. Carey taps it towards backward point.
It is full, wide outside off. Alex Carey reaches out and lofts it towards backward point. It lands safely as they cross for a single.
Full, sliding down leg. Green goes back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
It is a length ball that comes in from outside off. Green looks to block it but misses and takes a blow high on his pads.
Beats everything! Lungi Ngidi cannot believe it. A length delivery, that lands on outside off and shapes in off the deck. Cameron Green tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Flatter and on the pads, Carey tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Short outside off, cut straight to the man at covers.
Looped up, full and on leg. Green nudges it to the on side.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Floats it up, wide of off. Green leans in and defends it away.
This is sliding into the pads. Green tucks it to mid-wicket.
A short ball, going down leg. Carey tries to help it around the corner but misses.
Ngidi comes 'round the wicket and angles it into the batter. Alex Carey clips it to square leg for a single.
It is full, swinging in on off. Green defends it back to the bowler.
Wild swing and a miss! Fraction short, wide of off. This one flies off the deck. Cameron Green slashes but misses it completely.
Back of a length, some width on offer yet again. Green looks to cut it away but gets a thick inside edge.
Just a single off the over! It is short, outside off, with some extra bounce off the deck. Green shuffles and leaves it alone.
Flatter and on off. Carey flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full, on off. Carey reverse sweeps it to deep point for one.
It is full, on middle and leg. Green tucks it to the leg side and crosses.
Around middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket.
Alex Carey tucks it off his hips and rotates the strike. He moves to 96.
Loops it up, on off, blocked on the front foot.
Back of a length, on the body. Carey tucks it to the leg side off his gloves.
A length ball, outside off. Carey pushes it to point for an easy single.
FOUR! Powerful hit! It is a short ball, wide outside off. Green stands tall and cuts it through point for a craxking boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, wide of off. Green leaves it alone for the keeper.
Ngidi serves it on a length, on fourth stump. Cameron Green gets behind and blocks it out watchfully.
Alex Carey comes down the track and works this full delivery to long on for one.
On middle and leg, defended on the front foot.
Flatter, around off. Green goes back and defends it with full face.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Quite shor, around off. Green knocks it back to Keshav Maharaj.
Fuller, on off, blocked off the front foot.
BEATEN! Marco Jansen starts with a short-of-a-length delivery outside off, Alex Carey looks to cut it away but gets beaten on the outside edge. He needs to be calm and not lose his patience here.

HUNDRED FOR CAREY! This is his maiden Test century as well and what a time to register it too. He looked positive from the start and has helped his side to take a massive lead now. Coming to the delievery, it is short and outside off, Alex Carey punches it through covers for three runs. He is happy and his family in the crowd is delighted too.
On a length and on leg, Cameron Green tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Length again and on off, Cameron Green pushes it towards covers for a quick single.
This is on a good length and on middle, Alex Carey knocks it back to the bowler.
A bit fuller and on off, Alex Carey blocks it out.
Short and on off, Cameron Green knocks it towards mid off.
Flatter, full and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it to the off side.
Shorter in length and outside off, Cameron Green cuts it towards covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cameron Green defends it on the front foot.
On off, kept out.
Floated, full and on off, Cameron Green leans on and blocks it again.
This is on a good length and on off, Alex Carey knocks it towards covers.
Back of a length and outside off, Alex Carey cuts it towards deep point for a single. With that, the 100-run partnership comes up between these two batters.
Goes fuller and on off, angling away, Cameron Green goes for the drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full again and well outside off, Cameron Green lets it go to the keeper.
Another full delivery, on off, angling away, Cameron Green offers not shot at it.
This is pitched up, on off, Cameron Green drives it towards covers where Temba Bavuma fumbles a bit and allows a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cameron Green blocks it out.
A bit short and on off, Cameron Green moves back and pushes it towards short covers.
Floated, full and on off, Cameron Green leans on and defends it to the off side.
Shortish and on middle, Cameron Green keeps it out.
Gives this one some air, on off, Cameron Green prods forwards and blocks it with the outer half of his bat.
Maiden over! This is short and on middle, Cameron Green goes on his back foot and knocks it towards mid off.
This is full and on off, Alex Carey drives it wide of mid off where Lungi Ngidi dives to his left to make a good stop. They cross.
EDGED AND FOUR! Marco Jansen serves this full and on off, Cameron Green looks to block it but gets an outside edge as the ball flies past between gully and third slip for a boundary.
A bouncer, on off, keeps low a bit, Cameron Green ducks under it.
Marco Jansen bangs in a sharp bouncer this time, on middle, Cameron Green ducks underneath it again.
Goes fuller and on middle, Cameron Green drives it back down the pitch as the ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end and goes towards mid off.
Fuller again and on the sixth stump line, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Floated, short and on middle, Alex Carey uses his feet and tucks it uppishly but in front of mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off, Alex Carey pushes it towards covers.
Quicker one, full and on middle, Alex Carey revers sweeps it through point for a brace.
Flatter, full and on middle, Alex Carey uses his feet and knocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated, full and on middle, Alex Carey once again reverse sweeps it towards sweeper cover for one.
Short and on around leg, Alex Carey pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a hard length and on off, Cameron Green cuts it towards point.
Back of a length and on off, angling in, Cameron Green lets it go to the keeper.
Short of a length and on off, Cameron Green gets behind it and blocks it out to the off side.
Marco Jansen bowls this on a hard length and on off, shaping in sharply, Cameron Green watches it through makes a good leave.
Marco Jansen bangs in a bouncer, on middle and leg, Cameron Green ducks under it.
Floated, full and on middle, Alex Carey goes down and scoops it towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
A bit short and around leg, Alex Carey tucks it towards square leg for one.
Flatter, full and on leg, Cameron Green looks to drive it but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a brace.
Short and on off, Cameron Green slaps it towards covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Cameron Green drills it back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Cameron Green moves back and crunches it towards covers where Khaya Zondo dives to his left to stop it.
Full and on the pads, Alex Carey works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full again and on off, Cameron Green blocks it towards short covers.
This is pitched up, on off, Cameron Green drives it straight to short covers.
Another full delivery, on off, Cameron Green drills it towards mid off and scampers across for a run.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Marco Jansen finally gets his man! An unconventional dismissal and a fine innings from Carey comes to an end. Marco Jansen bangs this short and outside off, Alex Carey is caught in two minds whether to ramp it ir let it go and he keeps his bat hanging there. The ball takes top edge of the bat and loops up in the air, Marco Jansen calls for it and settles under to take a comfortable catch. Australia lose their eighth wicket. Alex Carey make that long walk back to a applause from the crowd.
Howout: c & b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Back of a length and on off, Mitchell Starc keeps it out to the leg side.
This is full and on off, Cameron Green blocks it out.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and on leg, Cameron Green nudges it towards fine leg and comes back for the second.
Back of a length and outside off, keeps a bit low, Cameron Green looks to cut it, but misses as the ball goes under his bat towards the keeper.
A slower one now, on a length and on middle, Cameron Green flicks it towards square leg for a run.
This is on a hard length and on leg, Mitchell Starc looks to block it out but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards gully.
Anrich Nortje bangs in a bouncer, on middle, Mitchell Starc sways away from it.
A bouncer now, ducked under.

FOUR! A fighting innings from Green. He gets his half-ton with an injured fingure here. It is short, outside off. Green stays back and slaps it through point for four runs. The crowd is on its feet here.
Short, outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Green ducks under it.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, wide of off. Green slashes and misses.
On of, defended out.
It is full, on the pads, Starc flicks it to deep square leg for two runs.
SIX! All the way! It is a short ball, on the body, Starc swivels and smokes it over the square leg fence for a biggie.
Length and on off, defended out.
It is full, sliding down leg. Starc clips it through square leg for a single.
A short ball, on off. This one climbs on the batter. Green hops and blocks it out.
Short and on off, defended with a straight bat.
Fraction short, outside off. Starc looks to chase it but misses.
It is full, on middle and leg. Starc whips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball, on off. Green defends it out watchfully.
A full toss, on off. Green pushes it to mid on for a single.
OUCH! That would hurt. Jansen bangs in a short ball, on middle. Starc looks to pull it away but it gets pinged on his helmet.
Mitchell Starc steams in and dishes a short ball, in the channel. It flies off the deck. Sarel Erwee keeps his bat to himself as Carey takes it at a really good height behind the sticks.
Nice shape on this one! It is angled in, but it moves away after hitting the deck, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Good length, outside off, it shapes away with some extra bounce. Sarel Erwee looks to defend but decides against it.
This one is on a length, sliding down leg. Erwee tries to help it around the corner but misses.
Another one that is moving down leg. Sarel Erwee is unable to get any bat on it.
Mitchell Starc starts his spell with a maiden and the crowd cheers loudly. It is a short ball, wide of off, shaping away from the left-hander. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
A dot to start with! A good-length ball, angled across the left-hander. Dean Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Short and wide of off. Elgar keeps his bat to himself.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Pat Cummins and company certainly believe that they have got their man here. The umpires though converge and take it upstairs to confirm with the soft signal being Out. Coming to the delivery, it is a short ball, down the leg side. Dean Elgar looks to flick it off his hips but only gloves it on its way. Alex Carey dives in front of him and takes a solid low catch. The replays later confirm that Australia have got their man here.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Back of a length, at 137 clicks, shaping away a bit. Theunis de Bruyn is happy to have a sighter here as he shoulders his arms at it.

A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! It is a length ball, around off, it shapes in a long way from outside off. Theunis de Bruyn decides to leaves it and takes a blow high on his pads. Surely missing the stumps.
Fuller one, wide of off. Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone. A wicket-taking over from Cummins comes to an end.
Finally, South Africa and Sarel Erwee are off the mark here. It is a full-length delivery, shaping away. Sarel Erwee punches it through covers and crosses for one.
Starc serves a short ball, angled across the right-hander. Theunis de Bruyn watches it sail past him.
This is much fuller, around off. Theunis de Bruyn gets it past backward point off the outside edge. The batters take three and Theunis de Bruyn opens his account as well.
Full length, around off, moving away from the left-hander. Erwee dabs it to covers.
This one is on a length, outside off. It holds its line and Erwee leaves it alone.
A short ball, outside off. It moves away with some extra bounce. Sarel Erwee does not chase it. So, 4 runs come off the over here.
Cummins goes full, outside off. Theunis de Bruyn tries to go for the drive but gets it to mid on off the inner half.
Theunis de Bruyn shuffles and defends this length ball to the on side.
Three dots in a row! Cummins bends his back hard and dishes a bouncer, on middle. Theunis de Bruyn ducks under it without any hesitation.
Short again, outside off, shaping away. Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.

DROPPED AT FIRST SLIP! Pat Cummins almost had his second wicket here. Theunis de Bruyn lives a little longer here. It is a length ball, outside off, shapes away a bit. Theunis de Bruyn looks to defend it out but only manages to get a thick outside edge. It flies low to the right of David Warner at first slip. He dives to that side, gets two hands on it but it spills out in the end.
An inswinging delivery, on middle. Theunis de Bruyn clips it to the leg side.
It is a short ball, around off. Sarel Erwee punches it through point. The batters take three.

LEG BYE! Wow! What a delivery. It is fuller, swinging late into the batter. Theunis de Bruyn is pinged on his toes here as he fails to flick it away. The batters collect a leg bye as the ball rolls out to the leg side. Australia do not take a review here.
A single now as this is pushed into covers.
Length and on off, blocked on the front foot.
This is outside off, left alone.
Three dots to end the over! It is much fuller, angling across the right-hander. Theunis de Bruyn prods forward and shoulders his arms at it.
This is full and on off, angling away, Sarel Erwee lets it go to the keeper.
Full again and on middle, Sarel Erwee blocks it out towards mid off.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and outside off, shaping away, Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Sarel Erwee offers no shot at it.
This is on a hard length and on leg, Sarel Erwee misses his flick and the ball loops up off his thigh pads down the pitch.
On a length and around leg, Sarel Erwee misses his flick again as the ball deflects off his thigh pads towards point.

Mitchell Starc serves this full and on middle, swinging in, Theunis de Bruyn looks to work it away, but misses and gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls towards square leg. A leg bye is taken. Thers is an appeal for LBW, but turned down. Pat Cummins decides against the review after having a chat with Alex Carey.
Back of a length and on off, Sarel Erwee taps it onto his foot and the ball goes to the off side. They cross.
Fuller and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn tries to reach for it, but misses.
Full again and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn slices it uppishly past point for three runs. He is looking unsettled here.
BEAUTY! Mitchell Starc bowls this back of a length and on off, angling in, Sarel Erwee tries to have a poke at it, but the ball just evades the outside edge and goes through to the keeper.
This is on a good length and on middle, Sarel Erwee looks to block it but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.

Pat Cummins starts with a good-elngth delivery, on middle, shaping in sharply, Sarel Erwee offers no shot at it and gets hit high on his pads. There is no appeal for LBW as it is going way over the stumps.
On a length and on off, Sarel Erwee blocks it out towards mid off.
Goes fuller this time, on leg, Sarel Erwee drives it towards mid on.
Back of a length and around leg, shaping in, Sarel Erwee once again leaves it and gets hit on his thigh pads.
Fuller one and on the fifth stump line, Sarel Erwee lets it go to the keeper.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a hard length and on off, Sarel Erwee looks to play at it but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
Mitchell Starc starts with a fuller delivery, on middle, shaping in, Theunis de Bruyn blocks it with the inner half to the leg side.
Good shape! This is full and on the fifth stump line, shaping in, Theunis de Bruyn watches it through and makes a good leave.
Full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn strokes it towards mid off.
This is on a good length and on off, angling away, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Length again and way outside off, Theunis de Bruyn lets it go to the keeper.
Another maiden over then! Mitchell Starc serves this almost on a yorker length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn does well to dig it out towards mid-wicket.
This is full and on off, Sarel Erwee knocks it towards mid off.
Full again and on off, Sarel Erwee leaves it alone and Alex Carey behind the stumps lets it through as well. A bye is taken and it is called a no ball for overstepping.
On a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn blocks it out on the pitch.
Length again and on off, shaping in, Theunis de Bruyn keeps it out to the off side.
This is on a good length and on off, keeps a bit low, Theunis de Bruyn looks to push it away, but gets an bottom edge on the ground and through to the keeper.
Fuller one and on off, Theunis de Bruyn squeezes it past point for a brace.
Another full delivery, on off, Theunis de Bruyn defends it to the off side.
Back of a length and on off, Sarel Erwee pushes it towards point for a single.
On a length and around leg, Theunis de Bruyn works it towards square leg.
Length again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn gets behind the line of it and blocks it out.
Fuller one and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Mitchell Starc serves this full again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller in length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn stays there and clips it well past mid-wicket for three runs.
Short of a length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn blocks it out to the right of short leg.
Full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn steers it towards point.
Goes fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn defends it towards covers. This pair has looked solid so far.
Pat Cummins bangs in a bouncer, on middle, Theunis de Bruyn ducks under it.
Fuller one and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn offers no shot at it.
This is on a good length and on the pads, Sarel Erwee flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Goes full and on the pads again, Sarel Erwee misses his flick as the ball deflects off his pads towards the leg slip region. A leg bye is taken.
Full again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn knocks it towards mid off.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and on off, angling away, Theunis de Bruyn makes an easy leave.
Mitchell Starc bangs in a bouncer now but down the leg, Theunis de Bruyn shows no interest to play at it.
Half chance! This is full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn looks to play at it but gets an outside edge towards second slip where the ball just falls in front of Steven Smith.
Scott Boland begins with a good-length delivery, on middle, Sarel Erwee works it with the inner half through square leg for a brace.
This is on a hard length and on middle, angling in, Sarel Erwee misses his flick and the ball goes off his thigh pads towards point.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Scott Boland once again hits the good length and on middle, Sarel Erwee is early into his flick and gets a leading edge but it flies through the vacant point region and the batters run three,
BEAUTY! This is a tocuh full and on off, Theunis de Bruyn looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn dabs it towards covers for a single.

FOUR! Scott Boland serves this full and on off, Sarel Erwee drives it firmly through covers but the ball does not have enough legs to reach the boundary. Nathan Lyon from cover-point chases it and collects it but the batter run four runs.
This is on a hard length and on off, angling away, Theunis de Bruyn leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Theunis de Bruyn lets it go the keeper.
Mitchell Starc tries for the inswinging yorker, on middle, but it is low full toss instead, Theunis de Bruyn digs it out towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn forces it wide of covers for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! This is full and on off, Sarel Erwee gently drives it away past the diving mid off fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length and on around off, Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn looks to play at it but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards third slip.
Full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn drills it back to the bowler.
Full again and on off, Theunis de Bruyn drives it firmly towards the bowler where Scott Boland gets a hand to it and probably saves a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn tucks it through square leg for a single.
Goes fuller and on off, Sarel Erwee drives it wide of mid off where the fielder comes sliding in to collect it.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and on off, angling in a bit, Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! This is full and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn reaches for it and slices it just over Usman Khawaja at gully towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Full and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn drives it down the pitch and Mitchell Starc tries to stop it with his left hand but the ball brushes his injured finger. No further damage done though.
Mitchell Starc bangs in a bouncer, on leg, Theunis de Bruyn ducks under it.
BEATEN! Mitchell Starc serves this full and just around off, Theunis de Bruyn gets tempted and goes for the drive but misses as the ball just goes past the outside edge.
Full again and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn whips it past mid-wicket for a triple.

OUT! LBW! Mitchell Starc draws first blood on Day 4! This is an excellent delivery to get rid of Sarel Erwee. Mitchell Starc nails the yorker, on middle, Sarel Erwee looks to dig it out, but is a bit late to put his bat down and gets hit on the toe first before the bat. There is an huge appeal for LBW, but turned down. Pat Cummins goes for the review, Snicko and Hotspot confirms that the ball came in contact with the boots first and Ball Tracking indicates three reds. Australia finally get the breakthrough and South Africa lose their second.
Howout: lbw b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: FOUR! Just over! This is back of a length and outside off, Theunis de Bruyn slices it in the air and just over third slip for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn blocks it out.
This is on a hard length and on off, Theunis de Bruyn gets a bit sqaured up and defends it off the outer half towards point.
Fuller one and on off, Theunis de Bruyn knocks it towards point.
Full again and on middle, Theunis de Bruyn pushes it towards mid on.
Another full delivery, on off, Theunis de Bruyn is solid in his defence again.
Back of a length and well outside off, Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on middle, Temba Bavuma blocks it towards mid off.

This is on a good length and on off, keeps very low, Temba Bavuma lets it go as the ball rolls towards the keeper. Mitchell Starc gives a warning to Theunis de Bruyn to stay in his crease at the non-striker's end.
Full and on off, Temba Bavuma drives it towards covers.
Another full delivery, on off, angling away a bit, Temba Bavuma looks to drive it again but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Mitchell Starc serves this almost on a yorker length and on middle, swinging in, Temba Bavuma drills it towards mid on.
Boland dishes a length ball, outside off, this one nips in off the deck. Theunis de Bruyn gets an inside edge before the ball goes on to stuck between his pad flaps.
This is an in-tucker, around leg. Theunis de Bruyn stays back and flicks it behind square on the leg side for three runs.
A length ball, wide of off, at 135 clocks. This one hits the rough and stays very low. It sneaks under Bavuma's blade as he tries to block it out.
Boland goes full, on off, shaping in late. Temba Bavuma gets a thick outside edge as he tries to block it from his crease. The ball goes through the gap between gully and third slip. They take three.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Scott Boland gets into the action here and gets rid of Theunis de Bruyn. It is a good-length ball, angled into the batter. It nips away a bit off the deck. Theunis de Bruyn stays back and tries to block it away with hard hands. He gets a thick outside edge and it flies to Steven Smith at second slip. Although, Marnus Labuschagne for a while thought he could gather it from third slip and makes a dive to his left but pulls his hand out in time. The ball safely carries to Smith who makes no mistake. South Africa are in a spot of bother here.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Scott Boland

Commentary: Length, on top of off. Zondo dabs it to gully. A wicket-taking over from Bola comes to an end.
Pat Cummins starts this over with a nasty short ball. Temba Bavuma hops inside the crease and gets it out to safety off his gloves.
Two dots on the trot! Swing and a miss! This is much fuller, outside off. It holds its line. Temba Bavuma tries to go for the booming drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, around off. Bavuma opens the face and helps it to point.
It is full, angled in around off. Bavuma taps it to covers and scampers across for a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Zondo gets behind and blocks it with full face. Just a single off the over. South Africa are under the pump here.
This is full and on off, blocked on the front foot.
It is outside off, on a length, shapes in a bit late. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Boland dishes this on a length, wide of off. This one holds its line after hitting the deck. Bavuma tries to block it through the line but gets beaten.
Fraction short, on off. Bavuma punches it to cover off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is an inswinger, full and on leg. Temba Bavuma takes a step and drives it down the ground. It beats Pat Cummins at mid on and races away.
Length and on off, defended out watchfully.
Cummins goes full, outside off, moving away. Zondo blocks it to point.
Good length, wide of off. This one flies off the deck. Zondo lets it be.
LEG BYE! It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Zondo misses his tuck. It goes to fine leg off his pads. They cross for a leg bye.
It is full, on off. Bavuma presses forward and blocks it out to point.
Full length, angled into the pads. Bavuma eases it to mid on.
This is full, on middle and leg. Bavuma blocks it out with a straight bat.
BEATEN! Floats it up, wide outside off. Khaya Zondo tries to push it through the line off his front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tosses it up, outside off. Left alone.
This is full, outside off, turning in. Zondo defends it to point.
Flatter and short, around off. Zondo taps it to cover and crosses.
Tossed up, outside off. Bavuma steps across and blocks it out.
Around off, defended to point off the outer half. A probing over from Lyon comes to an end.
A length ball, on off. Zondo gets it to point off the outer half.
Good length, outside off, jags back in. Zondo blocks it back to the bowler.
Three dots on the trot! It is full, attacking the stumps. Zondo defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, around off. Zondo hops and eases it to cover.
Short again, this time on fourth stump. Zondo taps it in front of point.
A maiden for Cummins now. A sharp bouncer to end the over. Zondo sways away from the line. This is Cummins' seventh maiden off his nine overs.

A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! It is a loopy ball, outside off. It grips and turns in. Temba Bavuma gets low and tries to sweep it away. He misses and takes a blow on his pads. The umpire shows no interest. Pat Cummins, Nathan Lyon and Alex Carey converge, they have a long discussion but decides to go against the review in the end.
On leg, tucked to mid-wicket.
This is driven to long on for a single.
Nicely bowled! It is tossed up, outside off. It turns in off the deck. Zondo tries to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Floats it up, outside off. Zondo defends it out.
On off, blocked into the deck.
A length ball, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Tad short, outside off once again. This one nips in late. Temba Bavuma trusts the bounce and leaves it for the keeper.
Another one outside off. Bavuma makes yet another solid leave.
Cummins serves it on a length, around middle. Bavuma gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
It is overpitched, on off. Bavuma pushes it to mid off with soft hands.

OUT! RUN OUT! Bullseye from the birthday boy, Travis Head and he puts South Africa in a precarious position here. It goes from bad to worse for the visitors. This is just silly running. Very poor decision from Bavuma here to go through with this risky single. It is a length ball, on off. Bavuma taps it to covers with soft hands and ventures out looking for a single. Travis Head charges towards the ball, dives forward and underarms it towards the striker's end to score a direct hit. Khaya Zondo is way out of the crease here. South Africa slip further.
Howout: run out (Travis Head)

Commentary: FOUR! Nice shot! This is tossed up, full and around off, Temba Bavuma thrashes it through covers for a boundary.
A bit short and on middle, Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Oh..that is very close! Nathan Lyon flights this up, on off, straightens a bit, Temba Bavuma plays for the turn and prods forward but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Quicker, full and outside off, Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Loops it up, on middle and leg. Bavuma nudges it to the leg side.
On the pads, flicked to square leg for one.
A length ball, around middle and off. Bavuma defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, around off. Bavuma taps it to point.
Three dots in a row now! On a good length, on fifth stump. Bavuma hops and works it to point.
Fuller, outside off. Bavuma opens the face and drives it towards point.
FOUR! Up and over! Cummins goes full and wide outside off. Bavuma slices it over covers and gets a boundary.

Cuts the batter in half this time. A solid reply by the Australian skipper. It is a good-length ball that lands outside off and jags back in a long way. Temba Bavuma looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the inside edge.
It is a short ball. Kyle Verreynne tucks it to mid-wicket from outside off.
Pushes it through quicker and full, outside off. Kyle Verreynne shuffles and eases it out to the off side.
Tossed up, on off, defended out.
On middle and leg, nudged towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely played. Kyle Verreynne gets off the mark with a boundary. It is very full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne reverse sweeps it behind point. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
Fraction short, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne goes back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
It is full, around off. Bavuma goes for the drive but gets it to the left of backward point off the outside edge. Nathan Lyon dives to that side and makes a sharp stop.
On off, defended out.
It is a length ball, in the channel. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Temba Bavuma blocks this length ball off his front foot.
Boland goes full, on middle and leg. Bavuma flicks it through mid-wicket. Temba Bavuma hesitates initially but gets a couple in the end.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Bavuma closes the face and blocks it out.
This one turns in a long way from outside off, on a shorter length. Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards mid on.
Flatter, on fifth stump. Kyle Verreynne gets behind the line and defends it out.
On leg, flicked into mid-wicket for a single.
This is pushed through quicker, outside off. It holds its line. Temba Bavuma tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle and leg, defended to short leg.
Back of a length, around off. Bavuma taps it to cover and crosses for a single.
Boland drags his length back and serves it on middle and leg. Bavuma tucks it square on the leg side.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Bavuma prods forward and blocks it to mid on.
Boland dishes a length ball, on fourth stump. It gets some extra bounce off the deck. Temba Bavuma blocks it out watchfully.
Good length, around off. Bavuma tries to punch it through the line but gets it to the on side off the inner half.
It is full, straying on the pads, Bavuma nudges it to square leg for a single.
Good length, outside off, this one flies off the deck. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Flatter and short, outside off. Bavuma punches it through covers. They take two runs.
Full and on off, defended back to the bowler.
This is full, outside off. Bavuma gets it to point off the outside edge. They take one.
Floated, full and on off Kyle Verreynne dances down the track and pushes it towards mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Temba Bavuma blocks it ff the front foot.
This is on a good length and on off, Kyle Verreynne keeps it out to the off side.
Length again and on off, Kyle Verreynne defends it off the outer half towards point.
FOUR! Nice shot! Scott Boland lands this short and on middle, Kyle Verreynne stays there and whips it away towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Fuller one and on leg, Kyle Verreynne clips it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Fuller again and on middle, Kyle Verreynne works it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Kyle Verreynne defends it towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is flatter, full and on middle, Temba Bavuma goes down and nails the sweep shot in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Floated, full and on off, Temba Bavuma leans on and blocks it out.
A bit short and on off, Temba Bavuma moves back and defends it to the right of slips.
Short again and on off, Temba Bavuma punches it off the back foot towards covers.
On off, kept out.
Shortish and on middle, Temba Bavuma moves back and defends it down the pitch.
This is on a good length and on middle, Kyle Verreynne hops up a bit and knocks it to the leg side.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Mitchell Starc bowls this on a hard length and on off, Kyle Verreynne looks to block it out but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards Usman Khawaja at third slip.
Fuller and on off, Kyle Verreynne looks to drive it but gets an outside edge wide of point where the fielder dives to his right to stop it. They cross.
FOUR! Good timing! This is full again and outside off, Temba Bavuma opens the face of the bat and slices it over point for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Temba Bavuma blocks it towards covers.
Length again and on off, Temba Bavuma keeps it out towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is full and wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne reverse sweeps it fine down to third man for four runs.
Loops it up, on off. Kyle Verreynne comes down the track and flicks it to mid on.
This is on the pads, clipped to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tosses it up, outside off. blocked out.
Short and on off. Bavuma goes back and blocks it out.
Floated and full, on off. Bavuma gets low and sweeps. Marnus Labuschagne takes a blow at short leg. They take one.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Bavuma hops and tucks it to square leg. They take a single.
FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and pulls it towards cow corner for four runs.
A dot now! This is full, angling across the right-hander. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
A length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne punches it through covers and collects two runs.
Good length, around off. Kyle Verreynne gets inside the line and clips it to mid-wicket.
Kyle Verreynne blocks this length ball into the off side.
Full and outside off. Bavuma steps across and defends it out.
On off, defended out solidly.
Fuller, on middle and leg, blocked back to the bowler.
Loops it up, on off, Bavuma defends it out.
Tosses it up, around off. Bavuma blocks it on his front foot.
Short ball, outside off. Bavuma punches it to sweeper cover for a brace.
It is a short ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne tries to play the cut shot but gets an inside edge to the left of the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, in the channel. Kyle Verreynne shuffles and blocks it out to safety.
Good length, angled across the right-hander. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off, angling away. Kyle Verreynne punches it through the gap at covers. They take three runs.
A full-length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma blocks it back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.
This is on a good length and around leg, Kyle Verreynne nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Temba Bavuma dabs it towards point.
Fuller one and on off, shaping in, Temba Bavuma blocks it down the pitch.
Scott Boland bowls this on a hard length and outside off, Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Length again and outside off, Temba Bavuma offers no shot at it.
Goes fuller and off, Temba Bavuma drives it well wide of mid off for a couple of runs.
Back of a length and off, Kyle Verreynne pushes it towards covers for a single.
Full and on middle, Temba Bavuma knocks it towards covers.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and on off, Temba Bavuma looks to block it out with soft hands but gets an outside edge as the ball goes on the bounce towards slip.
Nice bowling! This is on a good length again and on off, Temba Bavuma this time gets beaten on his defence as the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full and on off, Temba Bavuma defends it towards point.
Full again and around off, Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
On a length and on the fifth stump line, Kyle Verreynne lifts his bat up and lets it go to the keeper.

FOUR! Just wide! Scott Boland bowls this back of a length and outside off, Scott Boland cuts it uppishly but just wide of the diving Nathan Lyon at point for a boundary. Lyon is down and looks in some pain. He is leaving the field but Australia will hope it is no serious.
A bit fuller and outside off, Kyle Verreynne shoulders arms to it.
This is on a good length and on off, blocks it to the off side.

OUT! LBW! Scott Boland strikes again! Australia gets the much-needed breakthrough. Scott Boland serves this uch fuller and on middle, angling in, Kyle Verreynne looks to flick it away, but misses and gets rapped around his pads right in front of the stumps. There is a huge appeal for LBW, and up goes the finger. Kyle Verreynne goes for the review, Snicko and Hotspot shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates three reds. A gritty knock from Kyle Verreynne comes to an end and South Africa lose half their side now.
Howout: lbw b Scott Boland

Commentary: Fuller one and on off, Marco Jansen defends it towards covers.
This is full and on middle, Temba Bavuma knocks it towards mid off.
